\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could you just leave the table when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, you could leave the table when you wanted to, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would she put it on plates and bring it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Pass it around, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any special order you were served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not father first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I mean to say - 'cos - 'cos when he had - was working you see, the - the time, you see, there - she had to be - there to work you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You'd have to be fairly quick wouldn't you at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Had one hour you know, you got hour - dinnertime you know. One to two you see was dinnertime. It would be ready - it would be ready time - it would be ready time you got home, they knew your time of coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You wouldn't all arrive home at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No. Perhaps - perhaps father and brother would be away to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 On Sunday there was more chance of you all being round the table together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. But like I said, the whole family was never there one - one time I don't think. The eldest was gone you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about the younger brothers or sisters, where did they sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They used to sit to the table like and - I had two young - two - a brother and two sisters younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They would be at the table as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes. Well you see the - was you see when - come to the first was you see I was away for five year, and me other brother, he was called up too, there was only - only two two girls 
home with mother - and father in those days. Got a small - got a small household. Yes. And when I come back after the first war I could hardly recognise the youngest sister, her'd grown so. I come in the house, I said, who are you? She said, I'm your sist
er, youngest sister, Doris. Coo, I said, I - how tall you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  grow'd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How much younger was she than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 She's - she was sixty-five back in - in sixty-five back in May 19 - 1970. Yes. She was born in 1905, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So she'd be about eight or nine years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes. Yes. She's still here you know, she lives -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would feed them when they were very little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh mother would, yes, yes. See - you understand in those days - practically every child was born at home
. No - nobody went to hospital in those days. We all ten - all - my mother's ten children was all born at home. They had a midwife here. She brought - she brought me in the world, but - there was no such thing as going the - hospital for children, a lot o
f poor people couldn't - so they was all - practically all the children of my age was born a - born at home. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember anything specially happening in the house when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. But - this
 - this woman - this - she brought - she lived up here on the street, she brought them - hundreds of children into the world, this midwife, yes. All times of the night they'd come you know, she'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did she get paid for doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I think there was - she was paid, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Paid by the people involved or by the council?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I think the council, I - I think - perhaps - I ain't sure but if a person - we had to pay a bit like perhaps - not very much I don't think. If you could afford it. Of 
course the word - she said afterwards you never - never heard of the word - the word abortion in those days. No. If it - if that was - if anything was said in those days like they say now they - they - they says it's a crime to talk about abortions in the
y days weren't it. That's why - that's why there's big families. Oh there's any amount of big families in Buckfastleigh. Plenty of 'em eight to ten, eleven. Any amount.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Parents couldn't really afford large families could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They couldn't, no, 
they struggled on, but they was happy. Very happy. Jordan Street there especially was any amount of - any amount of - large families. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you get on with your mother, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh she was, yes, oh yes, yes. Good hearted kind, yes, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Very affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 She was very affectionate, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you be able to share any worries with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes. Wouldn't like for you to get into any trouble at all though, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about your father, was he easy to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well he was a little bit different you see. He wasn't the same temperament - you know, temperamental as mother but - you see, he was head of the family and had to work and one thing and another and - he liked
 a - little drop of drink and one thing and another and there wasn't a lot of money. And - had to walk to his works, it was a long way you know at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could you take your problems to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes, take problems to him, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they expect you to behave towards them in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, well there was no - very little - di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 n't have many rules, not in the house, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But they expected you to be polite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they expect you to look up to your brothers or sisters in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 We was all - all - all - you know, very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't have favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, no - all very close they are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would they say if another child hit you, would they expect you to hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well there used to be squabbles between - you know, different families like - fighting and one thing and another used to do like you know. We were obviously only youngsters and that - at school and one thing and another. But - they didn't 
like you to get in any scrapes or anything, or do anything like. Cause them any trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of person do you think your parents wanted you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well there's so - well - 'course there was so many. It isn't like if you've got o
nly two - up to two or - say just two children, it was easy to manage isn't it. I mean you had to find your way, when - when you get up you see - we didn't know what - I mean a youngster doesn't know what he - eleven or twelve don't know what he going to 
d
o do he. He don't think about the future, not 'til then, before that you - like from day to day and one thing and another, you just go on like other boy and one thing and another, then when you get up to say eleven or twelve you start thinking, well I sha
ll soon have to start work or - what - what shall I do and one thing and another and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever want to do what your father did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, I didn't, no, no. I - I was glad to go in a mill with - for the money and you see helping the parents wit
h, you know, getting older and getting other clothes and different thing and one thing and another and - I was - couldn't wait, you know, for to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you think your parents brought you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I don'
t think they - I don't think working class people they could like - couldn't say very much what they wanted and one thing and another 'cos they was - you know, like short of everything, and money - money and that. But - there was the smaller families, wel
l perhaps they thought as son should go and learn a trade or a daughter should - learn something like, but - when you've got a big family like - let 'em go, you know, what they - fall into I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Leave it to fate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. You see, my son, wel
l he's only son you see and he - and - he went in a - Buckfast firm to learn his trade 'cos - the boss said before he left school he said, you going to come down with me when you - leave school. And - that's where he went to of course and he's done very w
e
ll. That's the work - the works you know at Fore Street. And - of course he served his time there, that was during the war time, that kept him out of the Army you know, after that he went - down Gloucester. Yes, of course, that's only one, you get - you c
ould do it with one but when you got ten you can't - well there's seven girls and most likely you think to yourself, well - these girls'll get married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But they wanted you to be happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes. They did their best for you, I mean to say you - they got it on their hands you know I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did they think of things like swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they didn't like that you know, you couldn't - no, no. I never swore in me life I don't think. No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would happen if you did something your parents disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh you would - I used to get a smack sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Father. Mother would never hit, no. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did this happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, wouldn't say that, but - once you kept on a little bit like you know most families were like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose you cant' help that, with ten children there are bound to be some problems?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. Get
 in trouble say perhaps - get in somebody's field and farmer been complaining been chasing the pullets and one thing, he'd come and tell your father and - I'll tell the police that - been trespassing and chasing the pullets and - 'course the police would 
come to your house then. But I don't think I got many hidings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You haven't any memories of any time you thought you were unfairly hit or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No - well might have been you know. He'd been - he may have been in - he might have been in a - fa
ther might have been in a bit of a temper and I said something or other and - shouldn't have said anything, perhaps got a - smack across the ear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But it was all sort of give and take was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes. It was and all with a big family I m
ean to say you're - you've got something to do to control 'em all. It isn't like if you've got plenty of money, like - money's a big thing in these days you know, yes. It was - so much to buy -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 People after the same job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes. But there's on
e thing about it in this place, the - hardly any unemployment. No, you may find couple that - was a bit gone in - you know - bit - unfit to work or they didn't attend to work but - always plenty of work here. Always. Right up to 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about the people who had to go to America?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they weren't unemployed, before they pushed off, they wouldn't want to stay here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They did it deliberately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they did it deliberately. They only had their family when they landed out there, of course 
they had - they had relatives out there you see. But they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I thought they had to go because of the mills closing down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, no, no. No. No, they - they went because they'd got friends out there and they told 'em what - what was like in Americ
a, they had letters to say what it was like and - they thought to themselves, no good staying here, might as well get - get out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you say that you got the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one of them play a m
ore important part in forming your ideas? You say they didn't have much time to tell you things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, with having - mother - to look after everyone. Yes I think so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Both of them helped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes. Mother was very religious woman. She - every Sunday she used to go to the chapel. Yes, yes. She used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 To chapel rather than church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well yes, I - yes, chapel, yes. She was very religious woman. As I already said she was good}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 hearted, she - always liked to be - frien
dly with everybody you know, liked a good yard with everybody she met and stopped and speak to anyone, yes. She was a good woman. That's why I think that she lived so long you know. The type that would - over all the - all the children. Her never used to 
worry. About money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose it's all a state of mind really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes. She was happy and with all - you know, I mean ten children to bring up, what would they say today, present day, if they'd to bring ten children up? Drive 'em mad. And - 
no children's allowance or nothing. And 'course the eldest sister, the one that was home when mother was in hospital had to look after the house see. She was in there for several weeks and - I ain't sure, about fourteen weeks I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was this before she went into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, the younger one, the one - one of the younger ones didn't - didn't go away to Plymouth, she stayed here and went in a shop you know, yes. She used to look after the home then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well just as I started work. Thirteen. I went in to see mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So there wouldn't be many young ones to look after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - brother was - me brother was - about two years and a half younger than me. Then the next sister was two and a half younger than h
im and two and a half years - he was going to school. And I was thirteen when I went - well, you know, the Saturday as I was going to start work on the Monday, in November 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would birthdays be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not so much in tho
se days I don't think, no, with big families, no. They - they know the dates and one thing and another, say happy birthday to everybody, no cards or nothing like that I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no. Not - not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have anything special to eat like jelly or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I wouldn't say so, no. 'Cos there's so many birthdays you see. Tell you, there'd be twelve birthdays in the - well there'd be - yes, I don't think that -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you bring friends in on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No I don't think so. No. You - perhaps they'd say it in school to you like, happy birthday to you. Your birthday today isn't it, they used to say, yes. 'Course not - like - in classes - different class - us used to know our classes - their ages. 
I do now. You know, you start - one who starts off here, say January the first and - goes right up to me in November. I can remember all my - practically all in my class up - when their birthday - the day of their birthday I cannot think of mine. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember anything special about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well used to - hang up our stockings in those days. Yes, used to hang up our stocking all right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you get presents at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 We used to - well these - I suppose they used to -
 pay, you know, get so many presents like and - perhaps the sisters down Plymouth and one thing and another, different ones used to - send presents, come home like with presents for us for Christmas. Well the younger children used to have a present like f
or this - for - say the last four - older ones didn't want no presents, no stockings up, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of presents would you get in your stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - sweets and one thing and another mostly, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. We didn't, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Nobody played the piano or sang or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, didn't have a piano or nothing like that. 'Course the boys in those days - when they get up a little bit they used - have accordi}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  and go round the - in country go walks -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043 
 for walks, playing the accordio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 n and little bit of sing-song like the - out of the town, where you wouldn't - weren't disturbing anyone. You'd do that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not that I can re
member. No. They didn't believe in - they didn't believe in - you know, card games or anything like that or gambling or anything like that, no, no. Of course they didn't have the money then, they didn't think nothing about gambling on horses or anything l
ike that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would there be any books around the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well maybe a few books like, old books, one thing and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well for - poetry, reading and one - poetry and one thing and another. Yes. Books what's given to us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they be yours or your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, parents I reckon, passed down you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Any newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I - don't know whether we got newspapers - possibly we used to have one a week perhaps - the Totnes Guardian or something
 like that, that's all, the district - I think that's all they used to go in for, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Magazines or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 We may have the church magazine you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would that be the church or the chapel one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well, the - I think the most - mostly - I think the sisters and that used to go to church see. Yes, come from the Vicarage like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember your mother or father reading at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I think I remember father reading like, yes. He wasn't a bad scholar I don't think, father, he come from - fair family you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What was his family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Wilcox's family, I think he - I think he come from a - educated sort of people I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I think they were in the building trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not the same ones as these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. Father's brother's boys, they got on very well, one - one of them - think he's one of the first ones to build them bungalows out Kings Stayton there, the eldest one. The other one at Plymouth were builder and - the
y was all in the - in the building, like carpenters and masons they was. The brother's children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So they were skilled craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They was, yes, they was, yes, you know, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I can't say - can't remember that, no, no. But we - brother, he was a very good scholar, younger than me and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 The elder or younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Younger one. He was very good scholar and - he'd had a good - very good go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5397527\charrsid5841043  
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 ahead sort of youngster you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well when he - when he left school, 'cos he was - he was about fourteen when the first war broke out and - me older brother lost his partner, he retired I think, pretty older than hi
m and he - he was in the timber felling. And he decided to take me - younger brother with him, 'cos he was a big youngster for fourteen and they carried on right through the war, timber felling. Then after the war they - packed it up and went in the fell 
mongering. They were both there all their life then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well with the skins and one thing and another you know. Yes. Hides and all that. They were there for several years. Used to do the - little bit of timber felling at - weekends, for anybody wanted any but - I think - they worked too - too hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, I - oh in those days. No, I can't - no, I cannot, no. I can remember the vicar, I can remember the vicar's funeral
, I remember like as I say the Clements and pickering's, some of their people. I - we - like been going to church and - nearly all the children attended, at the church - the church at the top of the hill there. Yes. We attended - 'cos Clements, they was a
lways good to Buckfastleigh, all the - father and mother and the sons after. They was buried up here. Then we used to attend the funeral like the - all the church be coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they be gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they was gentry, they had plenty of money. I think he was in - banking concern in London, Clements.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But you don't remember a funeral at all in your own family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well used to go visit the neighbours like. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever go and see relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Relations? Yes, I have done, many I have done, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you go with your mother or your father or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - couldn't say offhand. But - of course you see all the - in those days you see you had to walk - it was all walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You said you weren't taking out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could you just go out and see friends whenever you felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. Had our - crowd you know, our little clique.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have to tell your parents where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh well I mean to say it was - in the district, was - like you see there was no buses, couldn't get out of the town very much, we were confined to this area practically all us - life, up - up to the first wa
r. I tell you what we done one time, while we was at school in 1907, well of course us knew the - the reservoir at Pegwell - reservoir was nearly completed you know, finished, like we was going to see the opening of it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That's where your father worked is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes. And a - young chap, just a very young - schoolboy was coming from home, his - his father was a publican, and he said that morning when he came in he said, why don't we all come out - to see the opening of the reservoir? He said, if 
you do, he said, I'll give you a pastie each. So we - all the class decided to - as we came out of school at twelve o'clock, decided to walk up - there and - all changed into our best clothes what we had then and - walked out there and see'd the opening a
n
d one thing and another. Of course, next day when we came to school schoolmaster had us all in front of him and stopped our - morning break for a month. For - for going - mickey - mickeying from school as we used to say in they days. 'Cos - today what wou
ld them do, they say - they - they praise you up for doing things like that wouldn't they, it was five mile each way you know. Us had a pastie each and saw the opening of the - in June 1907.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was a really big event was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Big event, especia
lly for our own district, yes, and all the Paignton people was out. Then - it was a big event. Well we - when we - ten and ten a half that's what we walked, we walked about five mile out and five mile back. And he - we had to suffer for it. For a month, e
very morning there was not one go out to play. Kept in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever go out with just your father on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I've been walks with father before now, yes, yes. 'Course in they days people could walk you know, I mean to say, when the - res
ervoir was on some of the locals was walking it there you know, they used to walk forward and back, that's ten mile a day you know. All weathers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember ever going on any outings with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I've been to - in earl
y days with the - local races and National Hunt meeting and - always on Whit Monday and that. I can remember going with father when I was up - when I was very small, up - 'cos you'd be out at Dean - Dean Marshes, I can remember going to them and - got wet
 
through before the second race and I come back wet through before - before the - before the third race and came back. Of course I was living in Dean then, I was very - I must have been very young. Yes. Of course we used to look forward to Whit Monday like
, there was always races. Well say - right back from 1884.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you ever go to the seaside or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 With the church. We used to have a - I should say have a day trip every - every year, to Paignton or Teignmouth, they used to pay l
ike. And - the - sometimes the - the Wesleyan would go the same day 'cos - by rail you know, G.B.R. and - we had a - pipe and drum band at school and - they always used to march us down to the station yes. Yes, the pipe and drum band. I know one time ther
e
 were - used to have a team for swimming side, I think there's three used to - swim against the three form Teighmouth and - down - pipe and drum band from the station. And they hadn't the - hadn't the wind in - Teignmouth, but when they came back waiting 
for them at the station there was a - wagon, that pulled me right around the town with a - young boys sat up in it. Our - our - our - what do you call it - schoolmaster was very much like that you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He was a good chap was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043 Yes, and every Anni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 versa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid687880\charrsid5841043 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
y or - say Trafalgar's day up goes the flag. And - all these - these what I'm telling you went to America, the young people went to America, they sent along the - American flag, stars and stripes. 'Course he was very proud of that. He get us
 all together and told us what the - this flag sent from America by - and he used to put it up Independence Day, up on the flagpole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How many teachers were there at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He was - he was one like that, remember our Anniversary. And always 
- when - when these boys left school you know he used to follow them up, you know, they'd see him you know. Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was he with the older children or the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He - oh yes, he was - it was a - mixed classes in those days. There'
d be seven - seven standards there would, one to seven. Girls and the boys different - they're all in the same building but not mixed. But he used to use his cane. To keep us in our place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Just the one teacher for the whole lot of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, 
no, he was the head. There were - and men teachers. Every class yes. But the infants boys got a woman teacher, but all the rest was men, yes. Two, three, four and five and - but like I say at school in those days we - we had a very good education, I think
 so. I mean thinking now looking back. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What age were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Three. They used to take some two and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 quarters sometimes. Yes. Three - three to - three to thirteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you went when you were three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Three, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You were never given lessons by your parents or anything were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. They wouldn't ever give none. I know - I can remember once when I was in the infants school she said to me, I think we sat a little bit of exam, I said, here,
 who do you think is top today? Top this time. And I said, I don't know. Her said, you're top the - this class. And used to have exams like every quarter and - end of the year used to see who had most points. Yes. I think we had a very good education comp
ared with what they do now. We never had algebra, not 'til us was in the seventh class, just before us leaving, just - start algebra, of course us never got into it proper because we was leaving at thirteen. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could anyone go on from that school to another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
You'd got to pay that's always the trouble. You couldn't - there was no - anyone went to grammar school had to pay. 'Course as I say, the rich and the poor. You couldn't go in - up to 19 - well, that's intended to be up to 1918, bu
t up to 1935 anybody - you had a place in the grammar school would have - you'd more than likely get to - goto grammar school if you could pay so much say towards the train fare or books and one thing and another. They would have a better opportunity than
 what you get if you couldn't - if your parents couldn't subscribe anything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did anybody in your family ever go on to grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, my son - went in for it and they thought he would pass or - thought three of 'em pas but when it came t
hrough to the - they allowed so many points to the youngest one, well of course his father was a - railwayman, he could - he could travel to - Ashburton - free ticket see. But - my son didn't lose nothing by it, he - during the war time he - correspondenc
e
 course with the big engineering firm in - at a college, in London. And he got his diploma so - when he left Wilcox's and went up to - up to Gloucester he just showed that one - yes, you can start when you like, he said, that - that one'll carry anyone. B
ut - hard to get - working class people it's hard to get to grammar school. Unless you had the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When you first started school what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I - I - I think - I think it was nine o'clock and come out at twelve. And com
e - and then two o'clock to four I think, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Even when you were three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I - can't remember when I was - you see, I can't - you can't remember when you - nobody - I don't expect anyone can remember theirself not before - what hap
pened before five. I don't expect you could. Only thing I can remember before I was five - was - King Edward's Coronation. I weren't more than five year old then, I was not even two. And at the park they put planks across the - stream there, and they had 
-
 lighted - they lighted a fire up with coloured papers and one thing - up the field. And they done the same in 1911 when King George's Coronation up the same field. I remember them. But the first one I can just remember, I was just about under five walkin
g across the plank to go up in the fields for this, then coming back. But the 1911 one I can remember very well - King George.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They-d be very big events?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes. In the - in the old days they used to have very good carnivals here you kn
ow. Used to have a - torchlight one in - say in November. 'Course you had to chance the weather I mean, and - all tradesmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s cars with - loom - weaving loom on it and blacksmith - be sparks flying. And all the ladies used to do up their - faith, hope and 
charity and one thing and another. And as we was boys we used to have to walk along carrying torches. Used to get the oil all over our hands.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who organised them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh it was quite a big procession, I can remember one in 1911. That was in - that w
as in November. See 'em dressed - lot of - lot of 'em were either Generals and Field Marshals and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was for the Coronation year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, that was - that used to do very often and the - proceeds used to go towards Ashburton hospital. Yes,
 yes. Oh used to have very good processions. 'Course a lot of horse - horse drawn things - vehicles in those days, you see, 1911 there weren't no cars about. But - it was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have circuses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, where Grovers Park is that used to - that was a fairground, used to get a fair there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid687880\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
say - about eight times a year. Yes. Yes. But that - but the trouble with that was you see they - the pubs used to be open 'til eleven o'clock and they used to carry on 'til twelve o'clock. Of course eve
ntually the Wesleyan ministers house right near Grovers Park, he complained about it - the noise and one thing and another, and - the chapel people, that's them who had the mill and one thing and another, they called a meeting, they all - or other organis
ations, Y.M.C.A. and different places too, protest against it to stop 'em there, of course - Y.M. said - it didn't interfere with the Y.M.C.A. and they win and - after that I said - get no subscriptions from my people. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 People used to enjoy the fairs did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Everybody used to go there, of course in they days they used to come out of pubs and one thing and another and they used to be fighting amongst theirselves you know. I think they had to close it down a bit. Yes, used to be going 'til tw
elve o'clock. Roundabouts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When you first went to school who would take you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh me mother. 'Course - in those days many children - young children like that'd be crying, they wouldn't want to go, they'd be crying all the way but - prese
nt day they - they want to go, life is different altogether. Yes. They didn't like to be left you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have very far to go to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no. Only just from Bridge Street. See I didn't start school before I come down here, I - I was thre
e years old when I come down from Dean see and I started right in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Is it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What you call a - well become the council then. Yes, board school. That was built in - '75. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Where did you have your midday meal in those days, would you come home for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, yes, oh yes. There was no - no school meals in those days, nothing - no - no - nothing really in school in those - no milk or nothing then I don't think so, not in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you think of school, did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I used to enjoy it 'cos I - I wasn't bad, I was a - arithmetic I was pretty good on, I don't say all the things but - I was pretty good on arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You say you liked the teachers, did you like all the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I liked 
'em, oh aye, bit of - bit of punching sometimes they used to do. But like I say the schoolmaster had cane and I can see him - hitting some of the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But he only used it when he had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, he - 'course if they - there was any
 rows in the school they'd - between the boys, they'd want to fight and one thing and another they have the - they wait for they come out, twelve o'clock, and go up on the - you know as you go across there, it's up that scaffolding. Of course some was one
 
side for some boys, you know, might be - holding up for one boy others for the other. 'Course and the schoolmaster used to hear a row going on you know he used to come across the garden and get over the wall you know, and that - that would stop it. But - 
but that's all our fights used to be in those days, to settle arguments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would the teachers try to stop these fights if possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They - they'd push off the teachers, this was mostly the schoolmaster would come up and - put a stop to it, 'cos he 
lived in the school - schoolhouse see and he could hear a noise and - step across the garden quick and get over the wall and - they'd be all off, they'd be gone. He would - he'd pick out certain ones - that'd come before him in the afternoon. He was in th
at school - I think he was there for forty year, that schoolmaster. Well he was connected with many things and he was connected with the Y.M.C.A., he was one of the - pioneers to get the Y.M.C.A. and he was President for many years. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did he emphasise certain things like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, manners, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did he expect you to be punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh you had to be there punctual, yes. You hadn't got - attendanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 , you hadn't got to stay away, keep on mickeying, staying away for 
- just for minor things. No. 'Course you see he knew all the parents you see. He knew every family the school - master and you see he knew - he knew - he knew your family, he knew - I mean to say in a close place like in a small place like that he know ev
erything about different ones you see. My father and - somebody else's father and - sisters and mother and - they knew everything about 'em you see. In a small community they're bound to you know. Whatever happened somebody else knew about, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about ways of speaking, would - they expect you to speak properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh we had to read something sometimes like. They'd ask you to read something out of a book and one thing and another and - and learning to sing. I think in exams sometimes you had a - 
somebody playing a piano you had to sing a few - a line or something, 'course - get so many points for that, in an exam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You had to attend pretty regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. If anybody - you came on - staying away from school, if you never went to s
chool attendance officer until about - going before the Court in Totnes. Magistrates in Totnes, they fine you you know for keeping your children at home, unless you had a - say sickness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would anybody start playing truant or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I have 
done it you know, some of em done it, yes. Yes. But as I say he was very strict the schoolmaster, he was. He'd help you in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When children did anything wrong would the girls get punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I don't - not so much as 
the boys, no, no. I don't think they was so - they - of course they - they was punished but not like the school - like the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How would they be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I don't know exactly, perhaps they go in a dark room or something like that. Well no, st
and up in a corner for so long, that's what they used to do and they - not - keep them in from play for ten minutes to stand up in the corner. I think that's what - that was their punishment. In front of the class - in front of the class like. But - I don
'
t - I don't think they - the teachers in they days had command. But - no, they had the sole command. And I think your life outside the school too you had to be careful because they knew everything what was - what you were doing you know. It come back to '
em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they ever punish you if you didn't get the sums right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No I don't think they did that but - in a class they - they - they put the - highest - the one that - the cleverest ones right at the back seat, and the - those who - right in front,
 yes, yes. 'Cos like to see their work, they could see their work there. 'Course they could soon pick 'em out after a few - few years, who was - who was the dumb ones and who was the scholars, yes. But of course the only trouble was you see, once - in a c
l
ass you know who the dunces was, you always look upon them, well that's a dunce. You know, the other boys would say, well he - he - he don't know nothing, he's a dunce. That's - that was only trouble. And of course at - in the school this affects them in 
their play. I mean to say like in a class you can always pick out the clever ones can't you, the sharpest ones and - the dullest ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you think the teachers ever concentrated on the good ones and didn't bother about the dull ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - the 
- of course lot of it was done on the - on the board like and - you had to - then they asked you questions like from the front - about history and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents show much of an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well, liked for you know, you know
, to get to hear that you doing very well, I mean to say, so and so's - was top of the - so and so was well up at the top of the class like, hear the boys telling - talking like. Yes. Or your sister would say, how did you get on with your exam, and one th
ing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So they were quite interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, was interested, yes, if you got on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they ever visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well of course - some - some of my sisters was at the same time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they meet the teachers or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, the teachers used - well I mean to say, outside the school or - they - they - you meet up with them you know. They - I know one of the teachers was a - bit of a - instructor at the gymnasium or the Y.M.C.A., one of the two, he was
 very good. Yes. But the - you always seemed you was under 'em like, they - they - you know, you had to - play safe with 'em like, you always got that in your head. I don't say after you'd left school and got on a bit you didn't take so much notice then, 
y
ou think to yourself, oh - well so and so's my teacher, he used to punch me in the back sometimes. But - at they times the same as the schoolmaster, you - you was under him, same with the people outside, like owners of the mill and one thing and another, 
i
f you saw them walking down the street in those days nearly everybody used to raise their cap to them, yes. And I think they looked for - you know, they thought you had to do it too Yes. And I know at political meetings at - couple of 'em was on - Conserv
a
tive committee, went on the platform and one thing and another. Well if you worked inside a mill you had to be careful what you said. Used to keep quite see. 'Cos you was perhaps - you may be living in their houses. Yes. And - but in those days they would
n
't let us boys go in the Conservative - when they were meeting at town, they wouldn't let us go in. No. But at Liberal meeting they let us all be in. If you can - if you managed to get in a Conservative meeting you just - kick up a noise, yapping or somet
hing and he'd come over and - get hold of you, out you go. But - at Liberal meetings you could - kick up a noise then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Wouldn't the Liberal organisers try to kick you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. They - 'course people all - there was the Liberal - well of course th
ere was only two political parties, Conservatives and Liberals. But as you say you see some fun when elections was you know, the Liberal members what they used to go over - and the Conservatives come out the - from the Town Hall from the committee meeting
 you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You didn't have any sort of Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no Labour party, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No trade unions in before the war. Not before - no, I can't - not before 1914, no, no trade union. I mean to say you couldn't 
kick up in mill, you couldn't say much in the mill, I mean to say you had to take what - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did that change after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It did when the court took over, yes. But honestly what could you do before 1914, you couldn't say nothing e
lse they'd push you out. Out of work. And perhaps you - if you'd been living in their house they'd throw you out, that's what had you to be careful of. You see they had got a lot of cottages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did anybody try to go against this and organise anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I don't think so, not in - you see, no trade unions - they're no trade union there. No. Not prior to 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So people wouldn't have any protection?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No, no. No. I say they had their good points you understand, they'd get - they'd get
 things and one thing and another. There were good points. They belonged to the churches and one thing and another and the chapels and - and they had to do with dealing with - anybody sick or anything they used to - tickets say for eighteen pence or two s
hillings - groceries from the church and they - Hammonds people - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
 Dovers used to - give 'em out like to who they thought was - should have had 'em like say, the mother may be bad with four or five children maybe the - maybe ill and - needed - something and they'd give 'em perhaps a - a ticket for two shillings}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid687880\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 worth of groceries. So they - they used to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So they were well liked were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, they used to be - it was - one family was connected with the church, another one to the Wesleyan
 and some to the Congregational. Oh they done some good. They was on nearly everything you see what was taking place like - Justice of Peace and one thing and another and court in Totnes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What made them get out in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well like the son
s weren't interested. They - one - one had two daughters, well she was - they - they weren't interested in the mill, the two daughters. The other son - two sons, one never worked in his life, the other one went to London after the first war. And - there w
as nobody to take over and - they thought it was time to get rid of it and they got rid of it in 1920. 'Course that was a big think in a way and see and he had retire - retire - retail side the other side of the world you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When you were at school did all the other children come from similar homes to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, mostly, yes, yes. Well those with money went to the grammar school probably after say when they got about twelve year old. Yes. Ashburton grammar school and Totnes grammar school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you ever remember teachers singling out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I dare - I daresay they - if you was - I daresay they had their - their friends - you know - their favourites, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But there weren't sort of glaringly obvious favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. I wouldn't say that. But - they had their favourites - possibly come a little bit better dressed, better - perhaps they take - take more interest in them you know than the others come poorly dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You didn't have school uniforms or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, no, no, no. But - in those days - everybody - every boy I mean wore a cap. No like they do now - they - well - any old cap you could wear, but - in those days you never see any - or men or anything,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  they all wore - hats and trilbie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
s and one thing and another, not like you do now, you never see - I never seen a boy not - going to school with no hat at all, no. Collar and tie and these - these stiff collars you know like. Yes. Short trousers and then - then when you got older knicker
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
kers and stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - you know what - just the - what you call the higher town and lower town. Higher town up here and lower town, us used to be - us used - th
ey used to be up against one another, used to play football against each other up on the recreation ground. But - always used to have that in our mind, well higher town's - higher town's best and lower town - yes. They always used to play football against
 each other. I think this used to call the higher town just above the Globe this way. All below that was - classed always was all lower town. They used to play football against each other. No fighting or nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember any children who were left out of things, always on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - I think sometimes you know they was - bit dull I think - bit left out you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any children who were picked on all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And some of them you know when you go i
n - used to go in a swim about twice a week, some of 'em would put their costume and - would never go in the water, just touch it with their toe and never go in, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember anyone who was very very poor and people used to laugh at them perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, that's the trouble with - youngsters you see, they - they didn't know what harm they was doing, they'd laugh at somebody - push 'em about and one thing and another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember any sort of really poor children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I - y
es, I can remember things occurring like that, yes, yes. Yes. But then sometimes you had - you know, other boys had to back 'em you know - say - pushing about a youngster who was a bit dull and one thing and another, somebody would come to his aid you kno
w, and - tell 'em to clear off. Although some like would join together - if they was - kept on that one boy they'd go and take his part they would you know, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You stayed at that one school all the time did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 All the time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You didn't go on to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, no, no. I left at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Thirteen. Thirteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you think you would have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You couldn't stay on at school any longer. Not there. You had to leave at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you go to any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, I did not, no. You see thirteen, when I - thirteen - 1914 - 1910, well - the war broke out - 1914, I was just - less than four years af
ter I left school, I was in - in the Army, first war. I joined the Territorials in - in June 1914, 'course two or three of us was Territorials you see and then - three years before that. And - said, shall we join the Territorials, three or four of us went
 
up to - not thinking there was any war going to break out or nothing, of course - that was in June, in August went away camp at Woodley Common near Exmouth and - war broke out on August Bank Holiday, of course us was right in it. From there us went up Sal
isbury Plain in September. Well all of us was there, all the - the fifteenth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 , the sixteenth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
 and the fourteenth - Kitchener came up there and asked them - 'course us weren't bound to go overseas, asked 'em to volunteer for to go to India.
 So that the regular troops, the time serving men, could come across to France see. And those who were going - of course - several of us did volunteer and - but I was one of the youngest, I was kept back so - I come back with the Second at Newton Abbot in
 1914. But - then they started forming a second }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
 to go then, like the second fifths, the second sixths and that - and the second sixths was one of the first to get - nearly up to the strength of it but they wanted - about two hundred more so - hund
red and twenty of us from the second fifths at Newton Abbot and about eighty from Cornwall from this - from Devon and Cornwall, made up a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  and we went December 1914 went to India and arrived in Bombay in - January the first 1915. But Kitchener told us then we'd go for twelve months and then come back but - and get orders, but us never - us did}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 n't come back, us went to - Meso}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 potamia, Palestine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You were out there for four years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was all right, that way, but - second and fifth Devons, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, I don't - I - I think - I could have been - or if you could have had bit better but I think we were - we - up to the present standard, I mean better than the present standard I think, I 
should - but my son's a good - he's a good man for mathematics he is, he's better than I am. But he had - like I say, he had correspondence course with - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't have that in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. They used to send down the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You think you got something out of going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, I think I - can remember - yes, I think we had good training in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You hear a lot of people now say school is a waste of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I don't think so. Well they've got different - they've got different methods at that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  school now for doing their sum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
s like, the long division. We always used to go to the left - say - hundred and thirty multiplied by thirty-five, us always used to go to the left, but they today they go to the right don't 
they. It don't make any difference but it - I see the youngsters doing it now. I could do them, yes. Oh I can remember that you know - for going on with - in details, things that - things that happened you know, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you ever remember going away for a holiday when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. Never - never, no. I think the first time I went - went to Plymouth I think was - about 1912. The Cup Tie then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That would be for one day would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was - yes, we used to walk from he
re to Brent and catch a train there, used to go then for about two shilling. And perhaps go a pantomime at the Royal in those days for a shilling up in the gallery. Come back at eleven o'clock, get back to Brent and walk from Bent home. I remember going o
n - when Plymouth Argyll played Machester United once down here. About 1912. Yes. That was - that was about 1912. Used to be me and a mate coming home from Brent, used to come the old road you know. Yes, gang of us. Or a crowd of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were most Saturdays spent doing something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well we - well football, we had - we had a good rugby team here. They used to play - us used to go and see them up - ever - every week. Yes, Saturday in those days in those days - oh I should say there would be team
s before this century started. Yes. Association I should say about 1906 or something like that. Quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
good rugby team here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What else would you do on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I don't think us do very much you know, under round and - us used to wander round
 in the woods and one thing and another. 'Course us used to play football in the streets in they days, before - there wasn't much traffic, before the policeman come along and shift us. You very often - in those days the policeman used to go from - start a
t
 the bottom of the town, stop ten minutes at one corner then he'd come to another corner and another corner. And of course we were up here, we - see - when we see him coming say, policeman's coming. Us used to run up the road and he used to give us a chas
e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you get on OK with the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, he used to chase us, he - he catch us sometimes, give us thump with his gloves. They didn't seem to have much to do in those days, policemen, no. Well there weren't no traffic, no cars and - no wat
ching traffic or watching cars or speed of cars or anything. And at night there wasn't many horse and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  horse}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 drawn things - not at night. At the present you see cars travel - all times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there much crime down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, wasn't a lot of crime,
 no. Us used to be - allowed to go in the - in the streets and we could play marbles. If there was any horse and that get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about things like gipsies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh there was gipsies - gipsies and tramps about in those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did the police do them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well they shift them off. They was - they had homes, I believe there was one at Brantham and different places, but - they used to - the youngsters was a little bit afraid of 'em in those days, yes. Oh gipsies used to come, selling brushe}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did people react to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well of course they got to - got to know 'em I suppose after a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So it was the same ones came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Still the same ones as they were, yes. Ashburton or just outside of Ashburton they used to live.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You read nowadays about all these councils trying to move them on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes. They didn't used to in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I would go - church - got to school - Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would that be the chapel one or the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I used to go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Your mother went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Mother used to go to chapel in her latter - latter years, yes, yes. Her couldn't get away with all the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would she go to church or chapel when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I don't think she went very much then but as we got older now - the rest of the - sisters was going away and one thing and - married and one thing and another, she used to go. Right up to - she was going when her 
was - when her was seventy-eight, when - when her was eighty I think, still going to chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But she didn't go so much in your younger days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not in the early days, not what I can remember. I don't know about the war time, I was away for five year. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How often would you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 She - she would quite the Bible very often you know, yes. Yes. Her could - things in the Bible her would say sometimes you know, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Even when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of things would she say to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Something about - as a hen look after her chicken - I forget now exactly the rest of it, yes. Oh she used to quote the Bible, I can't remember all of 'em like but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What time of day was Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Sunday school I think was about half past nine to half past ten. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you go to church from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Sometimes you go to church, yes. But, like I say, attendance was good in those}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 days. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You think this was because of the prizes at the end of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - that might have been in attendance and one thing and another. But I think the parents compelled 'em to you know, yes. And the minister always, you know, would - would know - if these - these children - oh these children don't go 
to church, he would say it like. They had so much power in they days you know, the minister and one thing and another, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did this apply to all the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well, they - they - but the Wesleay - Wesleyan chapel come - used to do well in those d
ays, there used to be attendance used to be - and they - of course they - lot of - used to be some young preachers -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Why do you think the parents were very keen for the children to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they thought - to be pleasing the - vicar I suppose and
 - and they know then too they'd be - out of harms way. Yes. Yes, I think it would. Yes. And then of course one thing - one used to do the same as the others you see, they heard one the same, they all go - go church together like, you go school together. 
Some go church, some go the Methodist, some go the Congregational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any sort of rivalry between the church kids and the chapel kids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No I don't think so. But - I - not - the Catholics weren't very strong then. I can't see no children goi
ng to Catholics, not 'til - not 'til say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't built it until after the first world war did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, no. Early in 1916 it started, yes. But then they seemed in Buckfast - they got some settled in Buckfast and then - they come to Buckfasleigh and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any sort of prejudice against Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
There was in the - early days. I can remember the Catholic preachers coming in 1912. Running 'em - cursing 'em and running 'em down to the lowest, and some of the old - locals you kn
ow who was Catholics, they went for 'em and one thing and another. They had a - they had a meeting in - outside a Buckfast mill there one night and there was a bit of - bunch over there with these people, you know, Catholics. And they had one at Wicks cor
ner. Running - running down the Catholics with what they had done and one thing and another. But I don't think it done the preachers any good. No. They still carried - they got very strong you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have to have special clothes for Sunday, did you wear different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh different clothes than working day, yes, of course I mean to say when you - went to school on working days and you'd be - in the woods climbing and one thing and another. Sundays, oh yes, you had this - bit of a best suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. Some people would do, but I know my mother wouldn't - wouldn't sew a button on, not Sunday. She wouldn't - do nothing Sundays. No. They - they was like that in those days. They wouldn't do nothing on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they think it wrong if you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I shouldn't, not - no, we wouldn't do anything what was wrong on - not Sunday, no. No, I don't think in those days there was so much amongst the 
boys you know - the swearing, I don't think so. I think it was different in those days. I - well - it goes to show I mean to say everyone was going to - church so much you see. And then in the week they'd go like the Band of Hope and different things and 
the chapel people would have - something doing Wednesday and Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So your social life revolved around the church really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, revol}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
ed round the church, that's the way you had to do it, that's - and I think I - what I can - remember, you kno
w, that - the boys didn't used to swear so much. They may - step away and have a little whiff - buy a packet of cigarettes, five in a packet for say tuppence or something like that and they go out quiet smoking but - as for swearing or bad language, well 
I don't think there was so much. But - it seemed if after the - after the war, the chapels and that they seemed to go in - the congregations and - less numbers and the church, I don't know why it was. The present days is very - very low. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Mother did, I don't know if father did, I can't say father went so much. But - on Sunday you see in that - of course the Y.M.C.A. was there in 1898, they used to - mostly chapel people, young - young men, they used to 
get - be up in the gymnasium for Bible class you know. That was a good - eighty or ninety of a Sunday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would this be different from the Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It belonged to the Wesleyan, yes. Held it up in the Y.M.C.A., that's a big room. In one of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you'd go to church, Sunday school and Bible class on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They could, I was - 'cos I was too young to go up there, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How old would you have to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I should say - started work I think thirteen or fourteen they used to be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you go when you were at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. The - that was before - but when I come back from the war that was all stopped, it was all, you know. I think the war done it you see that - they did drop back a bit then. 'Course they u
sed to have one of the leading lights, perhaps the schoolmaster or a Mr Furnier what connected with the chapel used to be - take us or - take a class of boys like. But after the war it was all different. After '18, 1918. Dropped off. Well today is poor yo
u know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How often do you think your mother would go to church on Sunday, would she go every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When - she got - as the children was gone, yes-, she used to, yes. Afterwards you know, when here got older, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever go on Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was that once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Once a year go away - go by train, yes. Paignton or Teinmouth, that's the only two places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would that be all e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 x}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 penses found?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That would - yes, and have a nice tea there and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of things would you do on these outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well go in the sea down there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any sort of fairgrounds and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - you could borrow a tricycle at Teignmouth. Keep on going around the green or - O
r - before those who lend you a bicycle come looking for you, tell you you've had long enough. Pay so much an hour. But in - I don't know if you know Teign-mouth do you, the green at Teignmouth - the Den they call it at Teignmouth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you say you used to go along to the Y.M.C.A. things on a Wednesday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Not - not Wednesday, no, they used to have it on a Sunday afternoon there. But the Y.M.C.A. then you had to be - you had to be sixteen before you could go there, I was too - too young. You h
ad to be sixteen before you was allowed to go. But they had-they had a lot go even so, in the - early in the century, on - right on from 1900 right up to 1914. You see, I wasn't - there wasn't - I joined them just as - just in January 1914. I just became 
s
ixteen then, I was - names had to go forward and - the committee you know and - had to decide whether they - admitted you as a member. It was nearly all - associates in they days. Members you had to be a - one of the church or - you know, one - but most o
f them was associates, they - there used to be distinction between members and associates. 1914, that's when I joined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you belong to the choir or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, I wasn't no singer. I was always a leading light for the Y.M.C.A. aft
erwards like. Right after the - after the war - I was forty years Treasurer. From '28 - 1928 to 1968, so I - I kept on with the Y.M.C.A. after the war you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You still go down there don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I still go there, yes. The schoolmaster was the leading light there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there ever a temperance club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 We had a Band of Hope. We - that was at church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you a member of that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I - they only say - they - of course they used to take the young pe
ople, well young people weren't drinking in those days, only just for the future I suppose, but young people weren't drinking really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You hear all these stories of families being broken up by drink and things, was there a danger of drink in Buckfastle
igh? Was the temperance organisation a strong one or just a little one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - fair - fair size - the church, it went on for a few years this Band of Hope I know, I - boys got older and then they drop out you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Is the Salvation Army down here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, Salvation Army, yes, yes. I can just, you know, the - in - they used to come round the street corners and - some one of their congregation would give the address and - say are ye come to join the Salvation Army and all that. They go fro
m corner to corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember things like grace at meals, was grace ever said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I don't think it - not in - not in many working class poor families I don't think. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you ever taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well was - was - taught at Sunday school you know, they tell you to do that, you see, and the - some did I suppose and some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have family prayers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not at home, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, not very much, no. You see - you see, the trouble in these fays you had to be careful what you - landlords and mill owners, well not - not to - let 'em know what you was and of course a lot of 'em didn't take no interest in it, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't even say it privately to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No. No, they kept it - to theirself. Yes, they kept quiet, yes, you had to keep quiet in those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So both your mother and father really didn't have any interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No. No interest, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they ever vote in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes. They voted in general election. But - come to think of it was - was both of 'em could vote that was - oh it's only my father - only the householder - father could vote, yes. Yes, that - that - that was in Lloyd George's time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Have you any idea what party he'd vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I should say Liberals, yes. Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It was secret wasn't it, you didn't have to say who you voted for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. I - I can remember 1913 - one of Isaac Foot's 
sons, that's a big Foot family, their father put up for the 1913, he was a Liberal. And doing a bit of canvassing he was here at the weekend, he - he preached - a sermon down the Wesleyan - in the Wesleyan chapel here, yes. Of course - they were Cornishme
n
 and most of the Cornishmen are Methodist you know. Of course and father - five or six sons he had you know, well known man. By he didn't go in, he just got - the - they had Lord Mahoney. Lord Mahoney, of course that was the father, in those days he was c
a
lled Francis - F.D. Mahoney, then he was made a got a Lord - but - only once the Liberals went in was in 1926, that was after this period what you tell, 1918, he was a Liberal Labour, Liberal trade unionist. And he went in by three hundred and one but tha
t was the first time the Liberals or anything won the seat for; oh - in this century. Yes and it's Conservative, easy, it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was pressure put on people around here to vote Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could - I could say that - they that had money thought 
they had to put Conservatives, they were superior to the working class, they always thought so in they ; like I say there was two classes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 If your father was a journeyman mason would he have the same kind of pressure put on him, to vote according to what the employers wanted?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No I don't think so much 'cos he - he'd do any odd jobs see, he wouldn't be with one firm for that time, if he was working with one firm he had to keep quiet I mean to say most of they firms they was Tories and - they k
new - they knew all your background you know, they knew all your family, they knew everybody - like in the village you see, they know what you do and one thing and another. And - you had to - play up to 'em a bit. There was a little bit of class prejudice
 if you understand, yes there was. They looked down on you you know, I meant to say you weren't dressed like that. You didn't have the money or your family didn't have the money, you couldn't dress like those, they thought they was superior.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you know if your parents ever felt resentful about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well you couldn't do nothing about it, no, no. Just go - carry on from day to day like that. But they always thought they was top dogs, you had to - raise your hat to 'em and recognise 'em and one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 thing and another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So your father wouldn't be a member of any political party at all,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh no, I don't - not in those days, no. Only ones used to speak at the - these Conservative meetings was somebody that worked - in another factory or something and like - didn't work something of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of person would he be,
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well a carpenter or anything like that, anybody from the Buckfast mill could come and have a - have a go at it - at the Conservative meeting, but - local people, they kept in earshot you see. And they had to hear it again next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would it get back to the Buckfast mill owner that this chap had spoken against the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They couldn't tackle him, no, oh, they got - they was different type of people 
at the Buckfast mill. No. That - that's only ones who could. Or farm - well of course farmers - farmers - nearly all the farmers was Tories you know. Yes. Oh there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So your parents wouldn't take part in any political activity other than at a general election when they voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, they wouldn't, no they wouldn't, no, no, they wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did your parents do when they weren't actually working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Like I say mother used to attend the chapel or the church and one thing an another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well of course father used to have a - like - like his drink. Yes. Yes. Used to in those days, like myself, say when I started work, well - you had to start work - you had to get out of bed just after five or say quarter 
past five to start work at six, well it seemed in those days this was all work and - work and sleep because you - you - you had to go to bed fairly early to get out - to get out in the morning. The same with the parents, they had - sometimes they had to w
alk four miles to - to the - father had to walk four mile to his work and - time he come back, perhaps he would be late coming back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Sometimes when he came back for a meal he might not have time to sit down for a meal, he'd have to rush through them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - well in - I mean to say breakfast and dinner early, you know, the same time because it would be ready, I didn't tell you I mean to say - in those days just had a fireplace and an iron stove. Yes, you know, from the fire like, you could fil
l the what do you call it and - cook vegetables on, iron stoves, weren't no gas or - 'course you had to go bed with - oil lamp or a candle. No gas or anything, you had a - oil lamp or a candle. And same when you were up in the morning early. And you didn'
t
 have much time to have anything first thing because you know - you knew two hours afterwards you'd be home to breakfast. Yes. And it was very cold getting out - the mornings, yes. Of course us weren't dressed like the present day ones you know, just scan
ty. Us could have done a bit more clothing and - a bit more fire I mean to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So really you wouldn't have much time for outside interests when you got home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, you see us couldn't go - you couldn't go the Y.M.C.A. before you were sixteen years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your mother ever go out to enjoy herself other than going to the chapel or the church, would she go anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I can't think of - can't think of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Visiting the neighbours perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh visit - she used to visit neighb
ours, of course that's - in a rural area - friends you know, neighbours was good friends they help each other in - you know, their troubles and one thing and another, sorrows and one thing and another, you helped one another. And borrowed from one another
. Yes. In a small community. You knew 'em all. You was all friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would your mother and father ever go out together in the evenings, on Sunday or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh used to go out for a walk and one thing and another, yes, they used to go for walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Various times you know, it all depends on the distance. I think when he was on the waterworks I think he was away for a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How long was he working on the Plymouth reservoir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 At - Paignton Waterworks? Oh I should think it would be about twelve months I think, the last twelve months of it yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would his jobs usually be shorter than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well of course the - the most of that was you see when navies was digg
ing that out first, 'cos I daresay he was on with the bridge what was across. The last, you know, that was the finish of it. 1906 and - part of - see they had a lot of navies digging it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How many evenings a week do you think he'd spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh well, I say - part of - part of the - that one at the reservoir, Paignton water on Dartmoor I think he'd be home practically - well at various times I know he went away Southampton to work, he'd be away there for a week. But - when he was working lo
cally he'd be home every night you see. Within distance. That was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did he find his own jobs or did he get told where to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh he'd - you'd got to find your own jobs. Yes, yes. They went all over that plenty of times you know. Like I say they 
didn't build a lot of houses in those days no. 'Til after the - after the first - this first war that they started building bungalows and houses, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they have things like working men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s clubs in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. Yes, at - yes, at the Town Hall they had the working men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s clubs, yes. Go and play billiards and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your father go down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, he - it was more like a ; the younger generation used to go there. Play billiards and one thing and another, I don't th
ink he ever - father never went to these places you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He'd go to the pubs would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He'd go to pubs and - well it was cheap, you see the cider and one thing and another like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How often would he go to the pubs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh he'd go one night I think. Yes. He would - couple of times a week I reckon, yes Specially week - like weekends like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your mother ever go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your father ever take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I don't think he - he wa
s so inclined. Of course he - we used to have a lot of things here, flower shows and - then there was cricket, football. Yes. Sports and Friendly Societies was a good help to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of things would they do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well like a club like, they give you sickness benefit if you was home. You get sickness benefit, had the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You had to put money into that to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - pay it like - what you call - you belonged to it like pay shilling a week or three shilling a quarter. T
hen when you was on the sick list you get so much see. About five or six shilling a week. And you'd get the doctor, that was a big - Friendly Society was good in those days. I joined in 1911. What we called the old}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 fellows, and still - still exist you know. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there a boot club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
A what? No I don't think - no, no. You could get - you could get it you know like by paying different travellers come, pay - pay a shilling a week or a couple of shilling a week and get - everything just - well like credit - present day, yes. Or clothing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever pay any money in towards a funeral or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I - that - we can put like a Friendly Society, yes, yes, that would come through the Friendly Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was it just your father who paid into that or your mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, I - yes, my - my father - only father, mother wouldn't. Yes, I joined in 1911, the Odd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 fellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your father ever go to the races at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. Well of course in those day
s you know there used to be - Whit Monday there was a regular one. Yes, yes. He'd go there. Most people - most of the people did in Buckfastleigh in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did he bet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I couldn't - I don't think he'd bet very much. I don't think he was - you know, betting man. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you get on with all your brothers and sisters, did you get on as a happy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Always a happy family, I mean to say it's a struggle and we had a struggle and one thing and the other but - most of the
 working class people had a struggle, that's who got big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 families, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any brother or sister you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh I was close to all of 'em like but - like I say the sisters went away early but the - every - ev
ery so often they used to come home for their weekend, just for the day, one thing or another, or we'd go down and see them. Yes. They thought - staying in Buckfastleigh they could get a job down there you see and they know - couple of 'em used to work in
 a mill that was burnt down, they went to Plymouth then with the other sisters what was down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When you were a child who did you play with, your brothers or sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Neighbours children in the road you know, yes, they - oh, in
 they days you see there was a lot of children about, they'd big families, you don't see so many now. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Whereabouts would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh play in the streets, play football in the streets in those days. There - there wasn't the traffic, no, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you play in other peoples homes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well used to go in like, yes, at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would there be any playing fields you could go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, recreation ground, yes, you had a recreation ground, yes. And cricket. Cricket wa
s pretty old. They're going on for a hundred years the cricket club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was free was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh you go in, yes, like that, yes. Us used to go and collect for a football. But - collect, yes, you know the big houses and one thing and another, get a list of people to buy a ball for us. They was very generous in that way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would there be any sort of club to organise it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, you had your own - you know, there were - between four or five of you, they say - go round and collect for a ball a
nd somebody had to keep the ball and look after it and one thing and another, yes. And when - when you got the ball you used to take 'em to some places to show 'em that we had spent the money and - they'd got the ball. Oh they was very good like that. Ver
y - go - go around the town. And then like we'd play - one part of the town against other part of town. Higher town and Lower town, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have a yard or anything like that to play in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, we never had no - no yard, no. Well there was 
no traffic, used to go just outside of town say about Deep Way, I don't know if you know Deep Ways, up past the Sun there. Us used to play there by the railings and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of games would you play apart from football?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Used to play cherry-go
bs, used to put - stones - stones - put 'em onto a stone and you get back so far and - throw a stone at it and see if you can knock 'em out, the cherry, you know, the stones. Different s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043 
ort of games. And played bustler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s from - from one light to another, af
terwards you know when they had lights. Bustglers us used to call it. Run from one to other and they used to try to catch us running from on - right to the other. That's right, yes, yes. Us used to go on all sorts like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh we used to get dirty. Nail - nail boots and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would happen if you got really messed up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh you had to come home and have a good wash and one thing and the other. You said something about when I 
started work. Well like I say that's - I started when I was thirteen. That was in - 1910. And - 'course less than four years you see the war broke out. And I joined the - in June 1913 - 1914, the - the Territorials, not thinking there was going to be any 
war broke out, of course went away to camp the August in 1914 and - during - August Bank Holiday the war broke out. Of course we went straight on from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have a part time job when you were at school? When you left school would that the be the first}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6512675\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 time you did any work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I - I didn't do none but - brothers used to do them. I - I know Walter, he went away selling apples one Friday night - round the town. He hadn't sold any but he - but the shopkeeper said to him, he said, you bit every 
one. He - he'd - he'd - he'd taste one to see which was the sweet and which was the sour. They used to do that shopkeepers, let them go around selling things for 'em you know, yes, go round town. Turnips and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 People would buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, they - people used to buy 'em, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they get commission on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh get so much, get tuppence or something like that, yes. Yes. And in those days the boys used to - collect bones anywhere, you could get 'em in the fields and one thing and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 
 another, and they - used to sel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 l 'em you know, they used to - spending money for theirself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you at school full time until you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, you had to go, yes, full time. Tell you it was - three to thirteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you didn't do much on the side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No, no. We used to - when I was - left - had school holidays or anything like that. August time, used to go picking wartle}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 berries over - over - over the moor, and selling 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was in school holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you get out there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
To the - walk. Yes, you'd walk, yes, five - five or six mile each way, yes. And that - that's in the seasons like, say - about August they come out don't they, yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you get the full time job in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well - they - anybody could jump in there. It was cheap labour. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you didn't have to have interviews and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No. Leave - leave school one day and in the mill the next. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did your parents think about you going in a mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh they was glad of it, I mean to say the - the bit money, they looked forward to it, yes. It weren't a lot but it all helped. And in those days when you start a mill the first day you had to go for the doctor to - medicals, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you have to do in the first job that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well on the job of spinning. But with older - older boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would that be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Spinning the wool. Yes, working a machine, spin the wool in to yarn like, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did everyone start off on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Different departments, some would go one department, some would go the other. And - and girls as well, you know, weaving and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What hours did you work first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Fifty-six hours a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 From when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes. Six o'clock to - eight, and you know, the ten hours a day and six Saturday. Go in 'til one o'clock Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Even for thirteen year olds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They had the eight hour day campaign going about then didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Just after the first war, came - came back - forty-four hours I think. Now it's forty I think now. But - fancy working - fifty-six hours for five shillings. They; call it slavery today wouldn't they, well they wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You got five shillings a week then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Got five shillings a week, that's all you got, yes. They wouldn't allow it now, they'd kick against it, they'd say it was like slavery wouldn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you keep on that rate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, we used to ge
t - used to get sixpence every six months. When I - when I left to go in - in - the Territorial camp that's just the week before August when the war broke out, I was getting eight and six a week. Yes. Worked out about a shilling a - shilling a year. Yes. 
'Course when I come back it was all different, the hours and wages and one thing and another, and things was different altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would it be six o'clock to twelve o'clock on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Six to one. Six to eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And have an hour off for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. You have an hour for breakfast and then nine o'clock 'til one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you get paid for these hours you were at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, no, only the - only your working hours, no, no. That made the fifty-six see. Not much more than penny an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have anything like holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Not in those days, no, no. Not prior to the war. I don't think anybody could - not in different jobs, I don't think - I think - they had holidays but they were never paid for 'em. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 In those days did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I mean to say us - us was young, us didn't think you know not in those days, just carry on. Buy the - I've imagines since now, all these years after, how small I must have been when I was thirte
en compared with the boys of present day. I used to think it was cruelty to send boys in that - the - the size could - well I must have been that in they days, to send me into a place - at half past six - six o'clock in the morning, used to go wintry morn
ings, you'd be cold - you'd be free}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
sing going down to work, we used to go in the combing department where they used to - they were all hours, they used to work - somebody used to go in and put the heat on and one thing and another, us used to go in put our
 hands on that to warm ourselves up before us went up in our own department. Oh I think it - I think it was cruel that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Perhaps I had a tanner or something at the end of the week, 'cos - of cour
se money was worth more you know. Yes. I mean, lot of things were a penny, sweets and one thing and another you'd get for a penny and - what would cost you sixpence now easy. Yes. Oh money was - was worth more, of course it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of things would the money you gave to your mother be spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Food mostly. And - well I suppose - you see they had the general run of the - with the - say with the baker, with the milkman. They used to pay so much every week, then they could carry on for the fo
llowing week, the butcher and that. They - they was very - very good. And I - I should say the doctors was - owed a - owed a lot of money in those days you see cos the people couldn't - for the children and that, they couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they do it through the Friendly Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Those - well, they that joined the Friendly - afterwards when they could afford to go and join the Friendly Society -.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How much would it cost to join the Friendly Society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh it was - you had to pay shilling a month at the least. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That was quite a lot really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, well - to give benefits for sicknesses, so many weeks when you was home you know, and - and get the doctor. But there wasn't nothing extra was coming in, you know, with the Friendly Society, for dental treatment or eyesight or nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you think many people just wouldn't bother to join the Friendly Societies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, they just - no, they didn't all join but - it's fairly strong you know. Oh it's only thing you could
 do, there's no National Health not 'til 1911 - '12. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh - oh they was - us was all in the same boat, yes, all got on very well, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did the older men treat you when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh they treated us all right, yes. But you see, what - what we were doing then as boys in those days, spinning and one thing, well men does it at the present day, no boys don't do it, it's all men. No. You see the - they don't leave school 'fo
re them fifteen then they go on sixteen, well they've given up. Yes. But lot of men don't take boys going in that age, they say I shan't go in the mill. But some of 'em got to go in and - they all want to be at that further education and one thing and ano
ther, want to get on different jobs. That's why - that's why they've got to have men to do the jobs you see, where - where it was all boys. After you got sixteen on they jobs you was generally pushed on in those departments what men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s jobs was doing, yes, you - they wouldn't keep it on 'til after seventeen see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of jobs would you go on to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 In - well in the - in the finishing department or - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you do in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Help finish - you carry the pieces, finished like, g
o through several processes - processes that you - to finish 'em like. Pressing 'em and packing 'em up afterwards and sending 'em away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was that a skilled job or semi-skilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well sort of a semi-skilled, yes. You pick it up as you go, yes, yes.
 And some go in the combing shop, well they're mostly men in the comb shop, there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Combing. Combing. Combing - where they wash the wool and comb it and make it into tops and one thing and another, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of jobs would be the skilled jobs in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - well you'd have to have the fitters or engineering you know to put the - look after the machinery. I wouldn't say as - you wouldn't say weaving was a skilled job not for women to - some got on better than oth
er. I wouldn't say - many skilful jobs or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They were sort of semi-skilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Semi-skilled - ordinary worker, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you feel about the work, did you get on all right with it? Did you enjoy doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I enjoyed doing it. Of course you enjoyed doing it because you had a little bit of money. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did it compare with school, which would you have preferred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I was eager you know to leave school to get you know on a bit. Yes. But it's different altogether now, s
chool's easier and - and milk, they get milk and everything to - but in those days it was very strict. Us was kept in our place with the teachers. They - I think we were well - well educated for the time you know, 1900 and just after 1900, I think we - I 
think we - education was very good, I mean to say, once you'd learned it you still remember it. But they got a better time now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It's a lot more free and easy now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh it's freer, yes, yes. And the parents - take interest in their children,
 anything doing at school they go and - help down the school. But in them days they didn't want your parents coming near, they didn't encourage your parents to come, not then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How did you find your employers, did they treat you all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh
 very strict you know, I mean to say you had to be there by time, no - no stopping home a day or two when you wanted to, no, you - you'd soon get the push. Cheap labour, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they ever bully you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well some of the -
 some of the bosses was a bit that way like, if you come in late say one morning, where have you been to, one thing and another they'd say, if you was only five minutes late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they be there at six o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they would always be there. Yes
. They used to be first ones there you see - to get it ready to start. 'Course they was thinking themselves well they'd over - you know, bosses, over you, they got the - position and one thing and another, but if you was a few minutes late they - where ha
ve you been to. That don't count for nothing if you had a cold or - they - ph there was a bit of discipline really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You did this spinning job until the first world war then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you do after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I come back to mill again only in the finishing department. Yes. But - at the same time there - there was no guarantee when I was going away in the first war us could have our jobs back again. No, there was no - nothing - nothing said that we should be - 
they'd take us back, when we came back or - somebody said, they want someone in the mill, so I went there and went in finishing department and stayed there for - forty - forty-three year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Forty-three years in the finishing department?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, I enjoyed it. 1919 to 1962. Yes. 'Course the wages was different then. But - 'course was - in 19 - in the twenties we had a bit of a - a slack period. The slump.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was that with the coal strikes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I think it
 was also reaction - reaction after the war like, yes, in the twenties, just early twenties. Reaction I think after the war you know, bit of worries and one thing and another. Before they settled - before the mills settled down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I don't think so, they wouldn't - these jobs on the - unless you - unless you was well educated I mean to say you could get away from here then, yes. But - jobs what you had to take on any job, the first one 
you come to I think. You didn't think about learning a trade in those days, well your parents couldn't afford to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you didn't do any sort of apprenticeship or training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you ever a member of a trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Trade - we - after the - after the first war the trade unions come in operation. Not before, I can't remember none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What union would you join after the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well I - I joined the textiles. We had the general workers
 and the textile, well I joined the textile. We had two unions, they'd still got two unions. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was it compulsory to join?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, compulsory, yes, yes, oh yes. Compulsory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever take part in its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes I used to be 
- what you call - I was a committee man and collector, used to go - collecting subscriptions, yes. For many years. Thirty year I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you feel that employers and workers had got the same interests or did you see them as different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I think in the early days I don't think he liked the trade unions, trade unions you know, I don't think so. No. Specially when it - specially when it started first, they - never been used to it you know, they - but - of course you had to agree to it
, I mean to say it was the trade unions all over the country then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Trade unions started in 1871 and they only got to Buckfastleigh fifty years later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But - I think you know - I - I - I think in all the West of England, so - so far as up Gloucest
er in all the textile industries like that - Wellington, that's old firm, Foxes and different ones in the Gloucester Valley and - never been trade unions, not in they days. That was all textile trades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did the employers try and stop the trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No I don't think - no, I don't think they did, I think - this - I think they saw that trade unions had to come you see. They agree upon it you see. Before used to fix our wages theirself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you feel in those days there were divisions o
f interest amongst the workers themselves, between trained craftsmen and the semi-skilled workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, I don't think so, you see - perhaps - as we - we - we were with our age group and we used to go around with our age group and one thing and the sam
e interests, us - us didn't - of course us knew the older ones, the carpenters and knew them all by names and one thing and another but I don't think there was any - any ill feeling between the trades you know. No. You see, you grow up with your age group
.
 Right through life you do you know. I can remember like say in 1918, well - those was born in 1898, say twelve months after me and - and 1899, they was called up just the early part of eighteen you see, never had much training and - they caught it. I bel
i
eve it was in - in a class below me, not my class, nine of 'em killed from this place. All about eighteen, nineteen. Called - that was coming through when they made their last trip - you know, trip - last attack, tried to break through the Germans tried t
o break through you know, the Western Front. And these poor youngsters - hadn't had much training, straight - drafted to France you see and - yes all - eighteen and nineteens, all in one class - about nine of 'em I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you join the local regiment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, the Territorialx. The Devons, fifth Devons this area was. Yes. Oh they was on many years before, they used to - in the old days I think they was called Volunteers, say back in 1910 and 1909, then they changed their name to Territorials. Ye
s. You could join when you was sixteen and a half. Probably they say - say you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
 seventeen, they'd take you, pas the doctor. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Could anyone not join if they didn't want to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, there weren't no compulsion, nothing like that. 'Course when 
the war broke out they was called up. They had to go then. 'Course the key - key workers, the owners, they - they had to deal with their businesses and one thing and another, they they kept some of 'em home what they thought you know they couldn't do with
out. They was kept out of the war a bit. Used to have tribunals I think but - lot of 'em used to - stay behind like they - carry on the works. Important ones. And of course they had some tribunals in the - before the war you know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 , people didn't want to go and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 one thing and another and of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there much meetings around here to get people to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well of course I - I was gone very early you see, I was away from - from - right from the war - when it broke out August the fourth I was away then
, Salisbury Plain and - I was India in - in January 1915 - 1915. Only sixteen and a half, sixteen and nine months, and there was some younger than me. Must have looked like - like a lot of boys out there. Boys battalion. 'Course all the regular troops had
 - left - left India, most of them, to go to - to France you see, the regular troops, that was their business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you were really taking the place of the troops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, which is a - as we see the transports - us as was going in could see the transports going back. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Would you say when you started full time work it changed your general attitude to life in any way? Do you think the gap between school life and working life made you a different person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I should - not when you get 
up a bit I don't think you know, you - you - you think you've left school and - going and earning a few shillings, well there you are. I don't think there was much difference.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did it make you feel a lot more independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well you - you feel lik
e you was away from school you could do what you liked afterwards, you - nobody to look after, I mean, to watch you and one thing and another I mean, school, if you went to school they know if you done anything. You was away from it a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever feel when you were at school that you should be out working because there was too many kids for you mother to look after?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, well - yes, too many, yes. Well - I don't think you know when you're about that age, like ten, you think about that - thi
nk about these things. I don't think you think before you get up about seventeen, then you think to yourself, I should like to earn a bit more money. There's - when you're younger I mean to say you - just too young to think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Some parents might say you've got to go out and work, it's about time you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Your parents never said that to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Of course they - there was no - they - some of the families you know, if there was any arguments they'd say, you've got to work or else
 you can go or something, when you got up - they wouldn't work and when they was about sixteen or seventeen they used to push off and join the Army or something like that. Can't live home here if you don't work. That was some of them. Father's used to - t
hat's how some of the fellows used to be in, yes. There was always some about you know and - didn't intend to work in those days, I don't say many, but you had to work for your keeps in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There wasn't the opportunity the same as today was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. No. No. But in this real country you get - you get - your neighbours and that were very good you know. Yes, you know each other and - you help each other and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you free to play with who you pleased in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. We used - a boy could always get in you know with others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There weren't any boys you were told to keep clear of or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Bad reputation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh you would do like, they - they - they'd say sometimes - mind who you
're mixing with, 'cos they - they used to know the - some the other boys was like. You get in trouble if you keep running about with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any rough boys from very poor homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I wouldn't say - I wouldn't say they - they was rough
 altogether. Not what you'd call rough. They didn't do things or do a lot of damage you know not the boys, not the rough boys, I don't think they did, no. Not compared with some of what goes on now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I - I joined the Boy Scouts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I should say about - about 1909, we had a very good lot of Scouts here. 'Course and one of the - one of the - we had the - we knew the sons of the Scout Master. Yes. Oh we had a very good Scout - organisation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well now we'd got - tying knots and going - walking out and - tagging places like, so many defending you know. And went - else went - used to go - once a year go camp up on the moor - away for a week see, August week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have to pay for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. Might have - might have paid us own, not very much, few coppers a - perhaps a week but - we'd have a good time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you'd be twelve or thirteen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, 'course - when us - when us got -
 when us got to work, thirteen and fourteen us used to only have the weekend camp like, say go the Friday night, the - then come back - that would be August Bank Holiday, come back the Monday night and start work again the Tuesday, yes. Yes, up on Scarend
on, Dartmoor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How many nights a week would you do it, was it generally one night a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 One night a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So did lots of boys join it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh a lot joined the Scouts. Yes, Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Then after the first world war you joined the Y.M.C.A.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes. Yes, when I - before the first war, yes, when I - when - when you get sixteen your names had to go before the committee. 'Course they know - they know you - some was barred and one thing and another, you had to go before the committee whet
her they accepted. I joined in January 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And you've been Treasurer of the Y.M.C.A.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, over forty year, yes. '29 to '69. Of course the girls used to have girls ckyb you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did they do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I - well they do all sorts of knitting and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was this the equivalent of the Boy Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Different - different - some of the Boy Scouts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't have Girl Guides as such down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not - not so - not in - those days. They got 'em late
r I think, yes. And I think they used to have mother's Union and one thing and another, for mothers to go there. Or as I tell you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You say the Scout troop was run by the mill owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, well he was - he was - what do you call it, leader and one
 thing and another, but any boys could - any - any of 'em - wasn't working at the mill could go. Oh didn't make no difference, you could have - from the - you the big - moneyed people they come - some of them join, yes, all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There was no sort of segregation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh there was no segregation, no. No. I think - afterwards - after - the curator, I think he - he took on after this - this one, this - our leader. Finish he went to Yorkshire. The church curate - he took a - took it over. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have any hobbies or anything when you were still at school, fishing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No fishing, but swimming and one thing and another, yes. Played football and played cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever collect anything, stamps or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I didn't collect no stamps, no. No, I don't think I collected stamps, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about butterflies or birds eggs or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - well I collected a few birds eggs but of course I - I gave 'em away but - you weren't allowed to. N
o. I don't think you are now, I don't think so now. I don't think you'm allowed to take eggs, no, no. I used to have a few, us used to go all odd places to get 'em you know, all sorts, yes. I don't think it is quite allowed you know, no. But - in those da
ys you used to see some lovely butterflies you know, different sorts. But today - there's only about two, the white ones you don't see many about here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any fox hunts or anything like that round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Fox? Oh yes, foxhunts, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Where did they start from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Different places, from all different - different places. It would be advertised you know where they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would take part in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well - well - when I was at school you know any time off us - used
 follow pem up so far as us could you know, they go too far for us, yes. Oh yes, foxhunts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you do anything like gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, I just - I done some gardening, early on, I done a few years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was this when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Just after I left school I took up gardening, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have anything like a school garden when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, we - we had a school garden, come to think of it - County, you know - you know where the ducks pond is ov
er - there is Tweenaways, all that's - all that was - that was the County gardens. We used to pay shilling for a - half a yard, land yard I I reckon, and they used to supply us with seeds in the summer and everything, see, about a dozen, potatoes, carrots
, peas, broad beans and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 This would be through the school would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
That was through the Devon Country, they - they appointed two men to do it, that was summer nights like and Saturday afternoon. We used to do gardening and then they used - they used to judge who was the best gardener and give a - gardening book.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were you allowed to have the vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You had the vegetables - all - each of us had a little piece of garden, that was your yes. And they used to judge you then to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever win?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I - I think I got a third, I didn't get the first but - since - after that I've done plenty of gardening. That was very good of the County you know to supply the seeds and - you know, something of each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There seemed to be quite a lot of activities going on for the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, supply the tools as well you know. 'Course that come the Devon County. Those two gardeners that look after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I never did, no. No, no, no, no. Used to be plenty of dogs and cats about in those days, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember having a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I never had no bicycle, I - oh there was a few bicycles with hard tyres you know but I never had one, no. Us used to make four wheeled trolleys and go up the road. And old box, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there many of them around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, several boys had those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So mainly you made your own entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh you made your own entertainment, yes, yes. Perhaps you'd go over to the chapel some nig
hts, the - lantern slides, shows and that. They had lantern slides, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were they free or did you have to pay to go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh - well - sometimes put a collection, put a penny in or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of slides would they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - all sorts of slides, yes. Used to have a lantern you know and that in there. Magic lantern, yes, different things - cartoon and one thing and another you know, different views, yes. Us used to do a lot of walking. Distances wasn't no - didn't mak
e no odds with the distance. I remember - in - 1909 and - King - King George V, he was Prince of Wales then, that's just - just before his father died, King Edward VI, he went to Darkby, you know, two - like about - when it was over Dartmoor, well that's 
a
 good nine mile. And we run - the Moorgate getting the - four in hand school through. They through money at us to catch it you know. Yes, that was 1909. 1910 we walk - we walked to Ockabite to see the race. Ockaby, yes, on Dartmoor, yes. Point - you know,
 like po}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 int to point sort of thing. Pon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
y racing on Dartmoor. Yes, used to be a big crowd up there, in those days it was all four in hands, no - no coaches, no, no. That was a fair walk. Nine mile each way. That was before I was about eleven year old, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose you were used to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, more often - like I say, when we used to be picking wortleberries we was - well - it's about twelve mile in finish you know. Six mile each way. Carry your basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you use that for, make jam out of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Make jam or sell 'em. Yes, make jam. But - like I say, they used to walk, boys used to walk a long - long distances in those days. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any theatres or anything in Buckfastleigh in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Used to have the travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 ing you know - comes here and stops here for three months in - in a field, and used to have different - programme every night. Used to pay about three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 pence to go in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of performances would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh all sorts, murders and different ones
 and - yes. Mostly murders. Yes, used to get a good audience there you know. They was here for three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And they changed the performance every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Every night they put the bill up for the week, yes. They used to lodge - they used to lodg
e here you know, at different places, yes. No, it was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did people think of them, did they look down upon them or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, they - they used to give them attendance, they done - they was very good. So far as I can remember, yes, th
ey was very good. And like I say us used to have the fair come very often. Half dozen times a year. For say from Friday 'til Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they have things like the dodge'ems?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, dodg'ems yes. And - what do you call it - the horses. Up - and do
wners is what we used to call 'em, yes, roundabouts. Roundabouts, yes. Shooting gallery and one thing and another. Oh used to have all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about a cinema or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not 'til very - I don't think - they used to - there was smal
l place down Kings Arms, you know the Kings Arms, that room on the right down there what is - that - that used to belong to the Kings Arms, used to - what do you call - pictures - all - Charlie Chaplin and all those in they days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When did they start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh they was - before the - before the first war I should think. Yes, I should say about that - 1910, 1911. No, no, I'm a bit wrong there I think. They was only - they was there in 1919. Whether they was on during the war I don't know. I was wron
g there, in 1919 they was on but - a couple of year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would it cost anything to go into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I don't think paid a lot in those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So there was quite a lot going on really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes. They used to come from Totnes and show these pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose a big fact was that you - everyone was still very tired by the time they'd done all that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, I can remember Charlie Chaplin in those - in those days. Couple of films they used to show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There's no cinema here anymore is there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there ever a cinema here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
There was one down near Station Road there where the car park is, up this end. Was inside the last ten years I think. Ten or eleven, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There wouldn't be any sort of bingo places in those days would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh no bingo in those days, I - like - well there used to be a few whist drives but I can't - can't remember going, not whist drives in those days. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember anything like a music hall - was there a music hall down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They were only in the big towns were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
At the Town Hall sometimes there'd be - a concert party there and they used to ask for local people to sing you know and get prizes and - and the audience - 
audience had to judge who was the best singer like, just - in - in common - in working with the concert people, see. They used to put that on to draw the - draw the crowds I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever take part in those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I couldn't - I was no singer, I was only a boy then but the older ones used to go up and sing you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about your parents, would they go in for anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They - now they'd go and see it you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would your older brothers and sisters ever do anything in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, I don't notice - there was only a few - used to be a few men. There was that old gentleman lived down - Pebmore in those days. He was - come from a good family called Peewee, you know, he was a bit on the easy side. He used to go u
p and sing, 'course they always used to clap for him, 'cos he had plenty of money, he gave - gave away a lot of money to different organisations. And course they used to - down Pebmore in those days you see was a paper}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 works and he lived at - pretty handy,
 and they used to pull his leg and one thing and another and say that they heard his voice in America when he sung on a Saturday night. It was - quite possible though. Yes, yes, it come true did it. But he had plenty of money and - he used to give it to d
ifferent organisations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was it mainly the sort of richer people who took part in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, just working people. You could go up and sing there - and be judged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How often would this happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh many - about - many times during the yea
rs you know, that - there was a concert party here, there's - singing on Saturday night, anybody like to enter - from the audience, could go up and sing - what they mind to and - give 'em a prize afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did all these things happen while you were still at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 School - just after I left work - left school, in the work - at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents ever give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no. Might have been - I said, might get tuppence sometimes or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And you'd spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember anyone outside the home ever helping your mother to look after the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No I don't - no, I don't think I could. I had sisters there you see. Young sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Any relations come round to help, if ever your mother was sick would your relations come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - you see I always - sisters with some of 'em working, you see, I had two sisters living in the town, well one's living home like, you know, living in with other people. But they used to - always come and help you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You say your sisters would help if your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, stay home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember anything about what would happen when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born? I suppose it's a b
it too far away to remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, yes, it is a bit far away to - but - my oldest sisters could always - give a helping hand you see, yes. But that's all right with a family you see, you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  always got somebody that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, an awful lot of - yes. After - later in life you see the sisters had married young, right handy you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about uncles and aunts and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well yes, from - from say the - say three mile, Ashburg
on she had - she had sisters, mother had sisters - several sisters in Ashburton. In Ashburton - several sisters in Ashburton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did she go and see them fairly often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Used to go occasionally. You could go by train for - tuppence ha'penny return. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they come over to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They used to come over and see 'em, yes, yes, in their younger days. Like they was married with families too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you see your father's side of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, we used to - his sisters come then from Tiverton, North - you know, the East Devon, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That would be a long way away wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Only about thirty-five mile. Yes, yes. They come - they used to travel - most people coming easier and going - coming and going would alw
ays be railway. Yes. They come with the railway, yes. Well like I say there was no coaches, no buses about in those days. Not for distance. Plymouth was - all - if you went Plymouth you always went by rail. Or Totnes or anywhere like that. Newton Abbot, a
ll by rail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parent shave many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, we had many friends, yes. Yes. We were a big family and we connected up, relations and one thing and another, you got a lot in a small place like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Whereabouts would you see them, at other peoples homes, or where would you see the friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well they come to yours and perhaps - Ashburton if you had any - mother's people, you were - you'd go by train to Ashburton and see 'em and that like. Well you could in - well I say it's three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
miles, you're nearly always bumping into them, coming out on business or something or other, you - you - I mean to say, there's no reason to go very often 'cos you bump up against 'em like. I mean to say when we were youngsters we used to walk to Ashburt
on on the Sunday afternoon just for a walk, and then you'd meet up with 'em. Yes. Oh you had to do a lot of walking in those days you see to - there was nothing else unless you go by train. And especially Sunday, the train didn't always run Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they have the same friends or did they have different groups of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Your parents? Did they have the same friends, share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I think they share - share the same friends like there perhaps and - lot of people - abou
t from 1900 stayed in the town you know, didn't go away, brought up their families and - side by side and one thing and another and - 'course the war - war upset things a bit but - lot of 'em lost their - sons and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, like - oh yes, yes, special ones like, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose your father would see people on his job traveling round wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did he ever bring any friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, I know he didn't - on
ce when they - was doing the - the reservoir on the Dartmoor Valley, he brought along a builder chap. Scotchman. Well he used to come in you see, the - all the - this working there used to come in end of the week to have a drink and one thing and another 
a
nd they used to come in and walk back again, of course they - father knew 'em all. And great thing in those days was - people walking. They didn't make no - make much you know of go - three or four mile in those days walking, no. They all took - took it i
n their stride. Or ten mile come to that. Remarkable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose some people would go by horse or coach or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Some got horses, like farmers and that, but - of course you thought nothing about it, there was no buses or nothing like that to 
- you - you had to walk. If there was anything doing five mile away you'd say, come on, let's go out and walk out as far as that. Yes. And the wonderful thing about it was the - they used to get with through in those days, they used to come and take their
 
overcoat - well, if they had an overcoat - and never catch the colds, they seemed to - just go and put their coats at the fire and - they never took notice of getting wet through or catching colds in those days, I suppose they used to but they - used to c
a
rry on and that, never hear 'em saying you know about 'flu in those days. The worst 'flue they had here was in 1918. About - us lost forty or fifty - lost about - forty I think in three - in three weeks you know, yes. I was away in the war. That was the w
orst time we had that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you think people might be open to disease if they're not getting enough food or working too hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 In those days you didn't - in those days you didn't - you didn't see so many people wearing spectacles in t
hose days. 'Course I know - and the lighting then was poor, I mean to say, you had gaslight in early days, round the streets and rest of it, but indoors you had candle and that. But the - I didn't think so many people in those days wore - wore glasses. No
.
 Well 'course - I suppose sort of luxury if anybody had - could afford to buy a pair of glasses in those days. Yes, but I don't - I can't see 'em now, going to school not many boys with - glasses on. Suppose a few. Of course and dental treatment, oh I - I
 know some of 'em with - bad teeth and one thing and another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, they'd come and see you like, yes. Want to know where so and so is and - they would come inside, they only want about - you know, for you to come out and play and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they ever come round for anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I wouldn't say that, no. We couldn't spare it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any special days or occasions, like birthdays, when neighbours would come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I don't think in those days ever I can remember the family used to keep up the birthday, you - remind you that it's your birthday and one thing and another 'cos - I remember in - I can remember in 1910 I - of course, I don't know how - how we come 
to hear that King Edward had died in May 1910, I shot up the stairs to the brother. I said, I hear King Edward's dead. I said, by the way, it's your birthday today too. Yes. His was - his was - his is the seventh of May, I think King Edward died on the si
xth of May 1910. It's your birthday today. But I don't think you know - I don't think they used to keep it up, they used to remind you of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 The people who came in would be more your mother's friends probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, more mother's friends, yes.
 My father had his friends coming to the house in - from different places like but - his - his cousins and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They'd come in casually, they wouldn't need an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, not they, not they - they - just as passing - sa
y, passing this way, thought I'd call in and see you. They might just come out from Ashburton or come from some town or something, I was passing, I thought I'd call in and see you, that's all, we - just - wouldn't stay you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did the same apply to neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. If they wanted something, yes. Or if you wanted something. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So your parents would go out visiting friends and neighbours quite a lot really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, well they do you know down here. The neighbours - 'course they made - ma
de 'em like mother would - meet 'em at the chapel of a Sunday night, have a yarn when they come outside, they - summertime stop at the corner talking, everything that was happening in the town and one thing and another. Some at the bottom of the town, and
 
higher part of the town, that's how they used to do it you know. As they come out - very religious they was you know those days people were. Yes, they used to go a church, or you know - wherever they went to, the - the churches, they - yes. Like I said - 
b
efore. Mother would never do anything on a Sunday, not sew or anything like that, no. She'd sew up to eleven o'clock for anybody else you know, but - Sunday, no. And father never - wouldn't - wouldn't chop sticks on a Sunday. No, they wouldn't do nothing 
like that, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 And you weren't allowed to go out playing football or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. No, wasn't expected on Sunday, no. Go to church or that you see. I think in - whether they was better but they used to attend churches and one thing and
 another, and they - they go - they remembered it was Sunday that - what they had to do Sundays and - no, they wouldn't - wouldn't do anything like that on Sunday, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What do you think your parents would do to make their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well of
 course in the week I mean to say they'd be patching clothes up and one thing and another and - patching your coat, doing odd jobs, socks and - 'course they couldn't buy a lot, they had to knit and - do a lot of knitting and - the sisters they did stockin
g
s for one thing and - they used to - they used to do a lot of sewing in those days you know. Girls - girls and one thing and another. Make a lot of their own clothes. They used to have a lot of dressmakers in those days, you know, they used to go in for t
hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your mother do this as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Mother was a very good sewer, yes, yes. She could do - turn round anything. She was very good sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did she make the family clothes or did she buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well you - like I say, some of the suits, th
e Sunday suits, you pay the packman, there used to be traveller come from different places - and they supply the suit and you had to last for so long and - always had to pay it out before you could have anything else like. Just like a credit system what i
s now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But your mother would make clothes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
She made - yes, those short trousers, yes. And skirts for the - girls. In they days parents was very handy, the women - they used to go and do a lot of their own sewing you know. They was very handy in those - not so today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You can't remember Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s Institutes or anything like that in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, no, this was a - there was a - Girls - girls clubs and one thing and another, the young girls used to go, girls club learn I suppose anything, knitting and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they ever play games or anything like that together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I don't - I can't remember many games you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, well you get a few - young men going around the - just outside of town playing accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 n like, have a walk around. Somebody would be having a little bit of sing-song well that'd be - out of the town that would be, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would your mother and father go along for that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, this was only group of - young men. Yes. One of 'em could play. I think there was - few gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 phones about, we didn't have one in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When neighbours or friends or relations came round what would your parents do to entertain them, would they just talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Just talk, yes. You see, you never go out - you never go out not for entertainment in those days you see. The small houses you know, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 People divide society into different social groups, before 1918 did you think some people belonged to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes,
 well - of course in - in - you see, being connected with the Y.M.C.A. after I was sixteen - closely connected with the Y.M.C.A. I knew everything that was going on - what was going on then. And of course the - the - the Freemasons have a - they had a Lod
g
e up over the building, on the top - top chamber there, that was agreement I think when - when the Y.M.C.A. was built that - that the trinity lodge of the Freemasons' would be at the top chamber, because most of them belonged to the Trinity Lodge was - wh
at you call the pioneers of the - was the ones that built the Y.M. Thought about - thought the idea out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of class would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh be moneyed people then. It weren't easy to get in I don't think for working class. But latterly, after t
he war, they could get in you know. 'Course they got to - got to go before a committee and that. But in those days this - it was all - all the gentry. Used to see 'em go with top hats on and one thing and another. Oh yes. Its only one class that joined th
at in those days. But after the war, well - it is mainly working class at present day. Yes. A big change in that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That's in the Y.M.C.A. now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 In - yes, that - that's the Y.M.C.A. now, they - they got their place at - as you go up the - up to
wards Dean you know where the Christmas House is. Yes. They're off on the right hand side there. Yes, that's where they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That's the Freemasons Lodge is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Yes. Used to be the Army Cadets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would you say the different classes were then in those days, just the two do you think or were there more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I think so, yes, I think so. I think the moneyed people was - they was the ruling body. And the churches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would you say they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - I don't say what they 
were but - people used to turn up at the churches I think the minister had a bit of power in those days you know what was going on in the town you know. They generally get a - get on the council, the ministers would you know. Yes. And those - had the mill
s, they was on the council too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would schoolteachers be in the same group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 The schoolmaster, yes, he'd be - he'd be one of the leading lights in the town. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would he be gentry though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - he'd be above - little bit above middle class wouldn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What class would craftsmen belong to, fitter and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I should say they belonged to the working class you know, to the - I don't think there was a lot of money difference between a carpenter and a - just a man working at the mill, not to regards to money. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember being brought up to treat people differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, we had to - oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, us was brought up to - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Touching your cap and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes. Yes. Do that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was this just to the gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, most of the gentry you know, yes. Well we always used to - us used to think they was little gods I think then people with the money, us used to think they was little gods. They was above us and us got to do what they say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you know then that they thought they were little gods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, not afterwards of course - after us got older us would - you know - us would pass them and say good morning but I shouldn't - that was gone after the first war,
 about that raising hats or that. Yes, I think so. It was put on a bit with us then you know, be on - be on the right side of them. They looked for it I think too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you look up to them really or was it just a matter of having to to keep your job and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well - thought to be on the right side, 'course they had - yes, yes. They was it. Well they was very good I think in - different - giving their money and one thing and another to hospitals, they helped you know - helped things. Hel
ped the churches. But - I say religion played a big part in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of class would the shopkeepers belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I said - I said there was only two - in the first place there was two, but - they were - you know, there was - go be
tween like. I mean the - those with the money had to go to these places and - working class, they go you see. Yes. They used to - make a living all right I mean to say in the shops in those days. I don't say it was all cash but - yes, I daresay they had s
ome bad debts from the poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They didn't sort of insist on getting them back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, they - long as you paid something every week they - they didn't like the idea when the Co-op come in you know at - the - the customers left 'em and - after b
een, you know, been served all right to go to the - down the Co-op to get the - you know - divi and one thing and another. 'Cos a lot - went and joined the Co-op you know. And the divi they used to save back perhaps for the - to buy something for a holida
y or - when the holidays come along, or Christmas, like a divi would be - down the Co-op so they could go down and draw it. That helped a lot on the - on this, you know, what they bought and one thing and another, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So it undermined the old traditions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, and the shopkeepers didn't like it you know, being so good to 'em all the years in the poor circumstances, when they got a little bit more and their children started to work and one thing and another and they started turning over to the Co-o
p they didn't like that idea. But the shopkeepers was very good to the poor people and - and the same with the doctors, I don't think some of the doctors were ever paid for all their services. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They would be paid through the Friendly Society you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Yes, well you see, yes, of course everybody wasn't in - in the early days perhaps weren't in a Friendly Society and you had to go to the doctor if your child was ill. And the same with - and the same with - the children being born you see, 
there was no grants then you know. No, no National Health and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would the farmers be gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, well just above the working class you know, they - they struggle - they used to struggle you know the farmers did I mean to say in those days. '
Course they had bigger - lot bigger staff on the farms then, several workers on the farms then you see. There was no combine harvesters and like of that, not to cut it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It must have been a hard life being a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, I should say it was hard work. Yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of people would you say went to the church and what kind of people went to the chapel, would they be different kinds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Two lots of people there, yes. 'Course they - they had their seats - well pews and one
 thing and the other special, of course they used to subscribe to these places and 'course they was the leading lights in the chapels and churches and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would go to which church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh it was - it was a Methodist you know a
nd - church and Congregationalist, yes - from - you know, from these classes, yes, they used to sub - support you know different ones, say the Hammond brothers, well one perhaps would be - go to Congregational and two or three would - couple of 'em would 
b
e the Wesleyans and - another one would be - go to the church. It was all - yes, it was all - they was the leading lights like in the - in the - these churches, yes. They'd subscribe you know, yes. Always looked to 'em for money I suppose the churches did
. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I should say - yes, yes, near enough the same standard of living, yes, they all - yes. 'Course and 
- you brought up with all these families and one thing and some of them - sort of all your life. Your - your age group. You still - you still know them I mean - they - they that stayed here. 'Course a lot gone on. 'Course us is talking about nearly sevent
y year ago.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So you don't think one group, like craftsmen, would feel superior to the another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, you wouldn't, no. If you didn't know I mean to say, if you didn't know what they was you used to think them all the same you know. If you did
n't know what their job was like. No. I don't think we - another thing, like I say, there wasn't a lot of difference in wages, not between the tradesmen in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were there any families who were thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they would pick - 
pick 'em out, if they had - if they had done something well you say, you expect it from they, they were always the rough part of 'em, they were - they do what they like, one thing and another. And they were kept out. You'll always find that in - in all wo
rking classes there's always some - bit roguish, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There were one or two round here were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
But afterwards when they growed up - you know they turned out all right. Yes. In those days you see several went and joined the Navy, in a local pl
ace like this. Yes, we had several - several Naval men of course. And lost several in the first war. Naval men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would that be the Royal or the Merchant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Royal Navy more - nearly all Royal Navy. Yes, take it into their head to join when they was 
about seventeen, eighteen and off and - hoping to come out with a pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there anyone you had to call sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well, all - you see it's all the - you know, the big - people with money we always used to say - call them sir an
d one thing and the other, yes. Yes. Oh yes, I - I think that we - the working class were very respectable, I mean, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would anyone say the same to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they'd - they'd called them say - Mrs so and so and one thing and the other, wouldn't say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Do you think your mother was conscious of being a member of a particular social class or group or was it just a part of life you didn't think about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, she didn't think about it. But - she would always respect they people you 
know, if they came to the door and one thing and another, if they - if you had any sickness in the house and they come to - say give you a ticket for - for - good - good bread or anything like that or cakes or anything what you want, or groceries. She'd a
lways you know, always respect - you know, pleased to - to receive 'em, to come in the house you know like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your father have the same view, did he agree with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well you see, the - the husbands you see they leave it all to their wives you see, these things. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was it possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No. It took - it took many - many years I mean to say - things altered after the war you know, yes, everything - altered after the war. When the families had
 grown up you know and - different conditions and the shorter hours and - and the National Health Service come in operation. More security. After 1918 it was better, when - when us come back. You see with the National Health Service, that was a big thing,
 
when you could - father or any - any of us could - was unemployed, us could go in and sign on and get a little bit of money. But - prior to 1918 people couldn't get nothing you see. Off Labour Exchange. And they had to go without you see. Possibly maybe w
eeks at a time, bad weather and one thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You say round here it wasn't too bad because there was usually a lot of work going in the mill or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, there was no - nobody was never unemployed or - or maybe a few that didn't want - didn
't like work but - no, there was always jobs, there was so much you see, there was the paper mills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How were these people treated, the ones who didn't want jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they used to look - they used too look down on 'em, he's an idler they would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But they wouldn't run them out of the village or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. But they used to call 'em, you know, idlers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well you really did, you know, they'd say, so and so's a nice - nice lady. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would that be talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well, the one who'd got the money - that would have perhaps - Hammonds. You see, four families - four families and - they was - oh they was a big - big thing in the town, the o
ff of the town you know these people. Yes. They seemed to have everything you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Can you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, they come - they'd come round right regular. Stop at each corner for about ten minutes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did they do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well, just to see that everything's going all right, yes. To pass their time away. 'Course and when they come up - they start perhaps down the bottom of the town and - kept the boys quiet down there
 then they would get up to Wicks corner you know, where the - where the fruit - where the ale house is now, well the White Hart - Globe and White Hart is, then go up to this corner here, stand up and see all the boys up Jordan Street now. Then when you ge
t
 out of there of course that's where all the plains is, they'd give us a chase. Go up they fields where you went last night. And then - perhaps come out for to be caught or else come down over the steps - of course one of us is coming up Fore Street again
, police would be coming down that way, of course we - dive up Plymouth Road, come across New Road and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you think of the policeman, did you get on O.K. with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They - they give you - well they'd give you a smack you know. With their gloves. But I got on all right with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman, if you did anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No. No, they were - that - they - of course they used to threaten you what they was going to do if you done anything wrong but I 
don't - they never called the police but they - they didn't like the police - they didn't like the idea of any - your sons or daughters being summonsed, had to go Totnes before the Court you see, it was degrading a bit you see. Because these - all these b
i
g people would be on the bench see. J.P's. That was degrading anybody going Totnes. Of course there used to be a lot of poaching going in those days. Rabbits and one thing and another. And which cases like that go to Totnes. Fine 'em five bob or ten bob. 
Or - people getting drunk had to go there. Of course that before their own people too, they'd say the J.P's on the bench, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How do you think the policeman treated the people, do you think he was firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, of course they - they only - 
of course they had trouble with - they used to come out of pub say eleven o'clock of a Saturday night and then - arguments and fights, well they had to part 'em and one thing and another, they - but - the boys was - us - us - us was playing about a bit yo
u
 know, us would only - policeman's coming, course you would run away up Ford Hill, gang of us you know, yes. I think they used to enjoy chasing us. Well they used to chase us - say let's go across that fields, they'd turn back and come down Fore Street an
d - meet us again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It was probably like a game to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, a game they - but - 'course they knew us all. And you was - you was a ringleader sometimes, they'd go out, they'd know which was the ringleaders and they could catch hold of them you know, give them a - across the ear with their gloves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Rent? You had to pay rent, yes. Yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you see anything of your landlord, was he a local man or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, he was a long way - he was - he was 
away from here I think, London or somebody - they used to have somebody to collect the money. The rents was low you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 He was very nice chap, would come there and I think he - time he had to pay
 rates and one thing - an - and repairs he didn't make - he didn't make no profit out of it you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you remember if you actually felt at the time that your parents had a struggle to - make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, yes, had a struggle, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
What did you think about the fact that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet? Did you want to do something about it or did you think it was one of those things that was nothing to do with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When you're young you don't think
 so much you see not 'fore you grow up - when you get up say about - thirteen, fourteen, well you used to think to yourself, I want to - earn some money and one thing and another. You don't think of it in early days as I say when you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  six or seven, you ju
st go from one day to another, you don't think about - how you exist or nothing. That's up to the older people - parents to solve they problems. You - but you know at times you got to go short - of food one thing and clothing the other, you got to wear yo
ur old clothes and - or you need a new suit, you think to yourself, well - they can't afford to get a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your sisters ever bring you anything up from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 lymouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes. They used to - help you know, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What would happen to the family if your father was ill or out of work, did that ever happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, you know like with - long spells of frost and one thing and the other they can't work, masons couldn't work you know for - weeks. I don't know how they used to - get on then
, of course the shopkeepers was good to us, helped us and pay it afterwards and that but - there's no - no signing on the dole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would the Friendly Societies help then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 If you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
 sick, if you'm a member of that you get sick benefit you see. Father was a member, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So perhaps you'd be looked after better like that then people who didn't join?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Of course not everybody joined the Friendly Society but it was good - like I say, it was a good thing, I mean to say for sickness - pay the doctor's bill that would you see. And you get sickness benefit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How much would it be compared to a wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, no, it would be - no. It would help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was he often out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well, the weather was - I don't know if the winters was wors
e - worse in those days or no but - they had long spells at times you know, the masons couldn't work. But - at the same time, some of them now I know but if they get frost in the morning they - they - they can do work out in the afternoon in these days. B
uilding and one thing and another. But in those days with frost they wouldn't work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I suppose they had to go along anyway, even if it was frosty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes. They - they go sometimes to their jobs and then come - go out and, no, we can't do none toda
y, it's too frosty, you can't - can't do no building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever get help from the Parish or any charities or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I can't remember but - there used to be a Poor Law in those days, very poor people could get a few shillings a we
ek, but - I don't think - our parents ever went to the Poor Law. No. 'Course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any sort of stigma attached to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they would - they go right into everything you know, they - like - like they was paying it - they - they that was 
in charge of paying the Poor Law, think they was taking it out of their own pocket the way they used to talk to the people that go there, some of them go there you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They were a bit sort of mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Means - what your means are, one thing 
and other. They was - like - they had the power didn't they, used to be able to say anything to people then coming for poor - you know, for poor pay - Poor Law. It wouldn't be more than a couple of shillings a week. - But they wouldn't have no hangers-on,
 they'd tell 'em to go to work, get work. Yes, no - no dodging.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They wouldn't pay you if they thought you could get work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, no, no. No, no. But they seemed to have the power in those days to say what they liked to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who would these Guardians be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they were picked you know by the - the Country, I reckon. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were they J.P's or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, it wouldn't be J.P's, it'd be men employed for that job, just like a school inspector, he was employed by the - the Country to g
o and visit all the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would they be gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well - little bit educated - they was little better educated than the working man they used to get these jobs. Hold 'em for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Were they local people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they may come say from - about six miles away from - do the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There wasn't any sort of building which you had to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh yes, you had to go to - say if he - he was a man from Totnes he - he'd come out to Ashburton then for to see - oh you had - he had rooms to go to and you had to be a - a certain day. Just this certain day that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they have a thing like a work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh the workhouse was - workhouse was - six mile away, Totnes. Totnes, yes, the workhouse, yes. That's where the old people had to go in 
they days. A poor job. Never sent our parents, not to the - not to the workhouse, no, wouldn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 That would be the last resort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh it was, yes. Yes. 'Course they'm provided for now you see, they've got these bungalows and they've got the 
- it's all - all better. But that's - yes. Too old they could be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043  no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 bod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 y to look after 'em. Go in Totness workhouse. That was kept up by the County you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have any children at school from the workhouse, the workhouse children would be educated as well wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I - I don't think they take the children there you know. That - that's the old people, especially for old people these workhouses, yes, yes. 'Course I know there was children - but - sent away, some of 'em in Doctor Barna
rdo's homes, London I think. Or sent homes for care, their parents died and one thing and the other, young people and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But by and large the parents would try and keep their children where they could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes. Yes. But like I say t
he old people used to - oh - too much trouble to look after 'em and - place - easy way out and - send 'em - to this work - house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any people in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, what about navies or gipsies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 We
ll they didn't used to like them coming around you know, no, no. 'Course in they days - some of 'em didn't work, could come around singing round the streets and collect money you know, they - they allowed them to do that in those days you know. Yes. But -
 but not so now, you don't - yes, go round and collect you know they could collect - make a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Where did these people come from, did they travel round Devon all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh they would come - you know, round about here say perhaps with ink - te
n or twelve mile they - they - didn't intend to work, they - they'd sleep in the hedge and one thing and another, these tramps and one thing and the other, they - but after - afterwards you see they went - they had places to go. One place, you know, they'
d
 go from one home to the other. But I did take notice of - when I was very young, a German band used to come around. But afterwards I thought to myself they - they didn't trouble if they took - collected any money or no, they was only - spanning I think. 
That's what I - I thought afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh I should say - back in about 1906, something like that. Yes. They used to come around - yes, playing in the street, but they didn't - they didn't seem to trouble if they took - you know, goi
ng with a tin, if they got any money at all. Afterwards when I got older you know when the first war broke out I thought to myself - they was only spies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What did people think about them at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well they used to like the - you know, heari
ng them. Go round every street, stop somewhere and play and go on again. I thought to myself, is queer, German band coming - round like that. But I thought to myself afterwards, they're only spies. That was all they were. The German band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Do you ever remember anything like rough music, banging lids and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I didn't see none of that, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Nothing like an effigy or anything being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh no, no, no. No. They may take it off - take somebody off, let's say - perhaps a counci}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 lor up in carnival sometimes, they'd take the mickey you know, but - yes. Just for a joke, 'course not many counci}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 lors would like it. No. About different things on you know at the - didn't pass in the council and one thing and another, somebody was up against it like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What kind of carnivals were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 Oh this was at T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 otnes, be tradesmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s carnivals and all sorts, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 How often would they have these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Only on say for - for many years - once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 This was before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
First war. Torchlight procession. Oh it used to be lovely you know, used to be good. And the women, they all take it in - take it up with paper, the wagons, it was all wagons you see in these days. Yes. Blacksmith, mason, barber. That was like tradesmen}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 s car. \{BLANK\} There's one up top, one down the bottom with big saws. Yes. Oh used to be a good carnival. Torchlight.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would this be summer or winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh winter, winter, in November. And the weaving loom on the - on the wagon. Worked from the wheel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Who organised that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh they - all - they could all join in then, they had a good committee you know, Secretary, Treasurer and everything and - all give 'em a helping hand. Yes. Used to be good carnivals.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 But by and large you think people were very tolerant of anybody who was poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh they was, yes, yes. And - anything doing or organised for the town like anything the carnival you see, they used to all join in. And if they didn't join in they - they used to len
d their wagons and horses - free of charge you know to - to parade around, to - take part. Yes, very good that way. They - well of course they people - they was very good organisers for - for the town. And they all used to join in. All - all ranks you kno
w. Working class and - shopkeepers and that to make it a success.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 I still lived at home 'til I - 'til the war, I went away to war. 'Course when I come back I got married. You see it wasn't a long time a
fter I - went work that the war broke out. You see, thirteen - sixteen and nine months when war broke out so there's only - less than four years. Still boys then. Seventeen - seventeen year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did starting work full time change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Oh no. No, I meant to say it was - you was still young then weren't you at thirteen and fourteen, well you were still young you know with your parents, no age at all is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 They was waiting to - waiting to go - well, waiting to go work too, brother, yes. That's all. Wasn't a lot of money you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they think of you as a big brother now you were out working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I don't know what they thought, you know, it was - there wasn't a lot of different between ages you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, did you still go along to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well I don't - I don't think I went - church so much, not after say - I think about fifteen, sixteen, before that I 
believe - well after I - I used to go after I started work for a little while. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, I seemed to drift away from it when you go - 'course like I say, I was - different from the time I left school - went to work you 
see and the time I joined the Army, I wasn't more than about three and a half years and - when I come back the war had all finished you see. When you get around the twenty - twenty - twenty-one mark - you didn't used to go to church then, not so much you 
know, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you take any interest in politics after you left school before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I don't think it - in a place like this they took a lot of - more than - more than at the election days. But in - in between I don't think us 
- took a lot of notice of it. I used to be interested in sport, football and one thing and another when I come back. In sport. Left that to the elder ones to carry out - regarding politics. But I used to attend the meetings. You know, the political meetin
gs if I could get in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Which ones would you go to, the Conservatives of Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I'd go - go both - go both but sometimes us wasn't allowed in the Conservatives. 'Cos we'd go in there to kick up a row to disturb the speaker and one thing and anot
her. That's what we used to do in they days, get the - but when you go in the Liberal one they - of course they liked to - upset the other speaker for one thing, 'cos they - they - they think they was scoring then. They wouldn't throw you out there, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 This was a Conservative area wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 The Conservatives - Conservative, yes, area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It's Liberal now isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Conservative. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You didn't really have any views on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No, no, no. Well I think you know it was the Lib
eral party perhaps as - you know like up against the rich people in a way you know, the Conservative, the boss on the other side, that's all, yes. Us was thinking that the Liberals was going to do something for us you see, the working class, if they get i
n power.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Was there any Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 No Labour, no. No. There weren't no Labour, not 'til the - war was over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You wouldn't come under any pressure to vote for certain parties because you wouldn't be old enough to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Wouldn't be old enough to vote, not 'til I come back from the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 So apart from election time and the odd meeting you weren't very interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Not politics, no. You see we didn't have - I don't think in them days we used to - much - as daily paper. I can't think of 
- maybe get one of a Sunday. Lloyds News, but I don't think in the week we used to have any paper. And of course there weren't no wireless. No television. Whatever come through -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 It would come by word of mouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, yes. Yes. From one place to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you do anything different in the evenings, after you left school and went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well I - you'd do the same thing. But after the war you see I went - gardening, I had a piece of garden and helped mother with the garden and that,
 growing stuff and one thing and another, before I got married. Took on a - took on some - land for gardening. Yes. I was always keen gardener. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 There wasn't much change really between being at school and being at work as far as what you did in the evenings were concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, no, not then. You see, the - you were still - come to think back over it you were still young, I mean to say, thirteen, fourteen, fifteen, you be just like going on from where you left off school. But - you was no age y
ou know. Perhaps it would be different if we went on school while you'm sixteen and then - left and - getting into - getting in to manhood then you see, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you go out in the evenings at all during this period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, went with a group you know, with a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would the group be from the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes. Well and - some of - yes, most of 'em - most of 'em did work in the mill, you know, youngsters my age like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Well just up around the woods, walk up around - have a yarn, or playing in the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 You'd have to be in bed fairly early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, you had to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 , yes, you never stop out - as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 late as - go to bed earlier than what you do - present day what children do at present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What time would you have to go to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
I'd say you used to have to be in bed by - by nine o'clock. You had to get up at half past five and - perhaps before that sometimes you know. It was - some - it wasn't much of a life but we took - we - we - we didn't know any difference
. Made the most of it, we didn't know the difference did we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you make any new friends about this time, were these boys you met in the mill the same you'd been at school with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Yes, the same age group - same age group you know, 'cos I know me 
age group now. But I - well I - I know their birthdays and everything, I mean, it's all years ago, I know when they - you know when they start, well the first one starts in January the first and goes right through the year you know, there's some been gone
 on you know, yes. Yes. As I say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you ever bring friends home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well they called for you you know, say, is so and so coming out? Yes. I'll be out in a minute, and one thing and another then - meet 'em up at the corner and - go for a walk or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have any particular friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Anybody you know, there were three or four of them. Decided what we'd do that night, play football, game of cricket, go up }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11949453\charrsid5841043 and play there. No, you was brought up with th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 em and you know - 
known 'em for years and right through the war and after and one thing and another and they still lived in the place and - it was your age group and that was the ones you always - you know, speak to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 What about the girls, would you know any girls at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh the girls was in - in the same ages you know, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Would you play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
No, they'd be on their own, they wouldn't play with you, they didn't used to mix in those days, not for playing or anything. No. Girls was separate from the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you meet your wife after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh after the war, yes, after the war. Both working in the mill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did they expect to know where you were at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 
Well they didn't used to trouble, not when you was about playing and one thing, they think theirself, oh you're in - you'll be in in a minute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9923787 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16607039 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1402753\charrsid5841043 Oh well you could - us was never what you call lat
e in those days, no. Us may have a Saturday night when the fair was there and we used to go to the fair like you know and - it was Sunday next day and -
